  nickname: jhn
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Deity of Jesus Christ'
      title: The Deity of Jesus Christ
      number: 1
      content: '  In the beginning [before all time] was the Word (<smallcaps>Christ),
        and the Word was with God, and </smallcaps>the Word was God Himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He was [continually existing] in the beginning [co-eternally] with
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All things were made and came into existence through Him; and without
        Him not even one thing was made that has come into being. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'In Him was life [and the power to bestow life], and the life was
        the Light of men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Witness of John the Baptist'
      title: The Witness of John the Baptist
      number: 5
      content: 'The Light shines on in the darkness, and the darkness did not understand
        it or overpower it or appropriate it or absorb it [and is unreceptive to
        it].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'There came a man commissioned and sent from God, whose name was John. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'This man came as a witness, to testify about the Light, so that all
        might believe [in Christ, the Light] through him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'John was not the Light, but came to testify about the Light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "There it was\u2014the true Light [the genuine, perfect, steadfast
        Light] which, coming into the world, enlightens everyone. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He (Christ) was in the world, and though the world was made through
        Him, the world did not recognize Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He came to that which was His own [that which belonged to Him\u2014His
        world, His creation, His possession], and those who were His own [people\u2014the
        Jewish nation] did not receive and welcome Him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But to as many as did receive and welcome Him, He gave the right
        [the authority, the privilege] to become children of God, that is, to those
        who believe in (adhere to, trust in, and rely on) His name\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Word Made Flesh'
      title: The Word Made Flesh
      number: 13
      content: "who were born, not of blood [natural conception], nor of the will
        of the flesh [physical impulse], nor of the will of man [that of a natural
        father], but of God [that is, a divine and supernatural birth\u2014they are
        born of God\u2014spiritually transformed, renewed, sanctified].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the Word (Christ) became flesh, and lived among us; and we [actually]
        saw His glory, glory as belongs to the [One and] only begotten Son of the
        Father, [the Son who is truly unique, the only One of His kind, who is] full
        of grace and truth (absolutely free of deception). '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "John testified [repeatedly] about Him and has cried out [testifying
        officially for the record, with validity and relevance], \u201CThis was He
        of whom I said, \u2018He who comes after me has a higher rank than I and
        has priority over me, for He existed before me.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For out of His fullness [the superabundance of His grace and truth]
        we have all received grace upon grace [spiritual blessing upon spiritual
        blessing, favor upon favor, and gift heaped upon gift]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For the Law was given through Moses, but grace [the unearned, undeserved
        favor of God] and truth came through Jesus Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Testimony of John'
      title: The Testimony of John
      number: 18
      content: 'No one has seen God [His essence, His divine nature] at any time;
        the [One and] only begotten God [that is, the unique Son] who is in the intimate
        presence of the Father, He has explained Him [and interpreted and revealed
        the awesome wonder of the Father].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "This is the testimony of John [the Baptist] when the Jews sent priests
        and Levites to him from Jerusalem to ask him, \u201CWho are you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And he confessed [truthfully] and did not deny [that he was only
        a man], but acknowledged, \u201CI am not the Christ (the Messiah, the Anointed)!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "They asked him, \u201CWhat then? Are you Elijah?\u201D And he said,
        \u201CI am not.\u201D \u201CAre you the [promised] Prophet?\u201D And he
        answered, \u201CNo.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then they said to him, \u201CWho are you? Tell us, so that we may
        give an answer to those who sent us. What do you say about yourself?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He said, \u201CI am the voice of one shouting in the wilderness,
        \u2018Make straight the way of the Lord,\u2019 as the prophet Isaiah said.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now they had been sent from the Pharisees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "They asked him, \u201CWhy then are you baptizing, if you are not
        the Christ, nor Elijah, nor the Prophet?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "John answered them, \u201CI baptize [only] in water, but among you
        there stands One whom you do not recognize and of whom you know nothing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "It is He [the preeminent One] who comes after me, the strap of whose
        sandal I am not worthy to untie [even as His slave].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'These things occurred in Bethany across the Jordan [at the Jordan
        River crossing], where John was baptizing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "The next day he saw Jesus coming to him and said, \u201CLook! The
        Lamb of God who takes away the sin of the world! "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "This is He on behalf of whom I said, \u2018After me comes a Man who
        has a higher rank than I and has priority over me, for He existed before
        me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "I did not recognize Him [as the Messiah]; but I came baptizing in
        water so that He would be [publicly] revealed to Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "John gave [further] evidence [testifying officially for the record,
        with validity and relevance], saying, \u201CI have seen the Spirit descending
        as a dove out of heaven, and He remained upon Him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "I did not recognize Him [as the Messiah], but He who sent me to baptize
        in water said to me, \u2018He upon whom you see the Spirit descend and remain,
        this One is He who baptizes with the Holy Spirit.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: "34: Jesus\u2019 Public Ministry, First Converts"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Public Ministry, First Converts"
      number: 34
      content: "I myself have [actually] seen [that happen], and my testimony is
        that this is the Son of God!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Again the next day John was standing with two of his disciples, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "and he looked at Jesus as He walked along, and said, \u201CLook!
        The Lamb of God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'The two disciples heard him say this, and they followed Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Jesus turned and saw them following Him, and asked them, <JESUS>\u201CWhat
        do you want?\u201D</JESUS> They answered Him, \u201CRabbi (which translated
        means Teacher), where are You staying?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CCome, and you will see.\u201D</JESUS>
        So they went [with Him] and saw where He was staying; and they stayed with
        Him that day, for it was about the tenth hour. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "One of the two who heard what John said and [as a result] followed
        Jesus was Andrew, Simon Peter\u2019s brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "He first looked for and found his own brother Simon and told him,
        \u201CWe have found the Messiah\u201D (which translated means the Christ). "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Andrew brought Simon to Jesus. Jesus looked at him and said, <JESUS>\u201CYou
        are Simon the son of John. You shall be called Cephas</JESUS> (which is translated
        Peter).\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "The next day Jesus decided to go into Galilee, and He found Philip
        and said to him, <JESUS>\u201CFollow Me</JESUS> [as My disciple, accepting
        Me as your Master and Teacher, and walking the same path of life that I walk].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Now Philip was from Bethsaida, the city of Andrew and Peter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "Philip found Nathanael and told him, \u201CWe have found the One
        Moses in the Law and also the Prophets wrote about\u2014Jesus from Nazareth,
        the son of Joseph [according to public record].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "Nathanael answered him, \u201CCan anything good come out of Nazareth?\u201D
        Philip replied, \u201CCome and see.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Jesus saw Nathanael coming toward Him, and said of him, <JESUS>\u201CHere
        is an Israelite indeed</JESUS> [a true descendant of Jacob], <JESUS>in whom
        there is no guile </JESUS>nor deceit nor duplicity!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Nathanael said to Jesus, \u201CHow do You know [these things about]
        me?\u201D Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CBefore Philip called you, when you
        were still under the fig tree, I saw you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Nathanael answered, \u201CRabbi (Teacher), You are the Son of God;
        You are the King of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CBecause I said to you that I saw you
        under the fig tree, do you believe</JESUS> [in Me]? <JESUS>You will see greater
        things than this.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Then He said to him, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly
        say to you, you will see heaven opened and the angels of God ascending and
        descending on the Son of Man [the bridge between heaven and earth].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Miracle at Cana'
      title: Miracle at Cana
      number: 1
      content: '  On the third day there was a wedding at Cana of Galilee, and the
        mother of Jesus was there; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and both Jesus and His disciples were invited to the wedding. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "When the wine was all gone, the mother of Jesus said to Him, \u201CThey
        have no more wine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jesus said to her, \u201C[Dear] <JESUS>woman, </JESUS><JESUS>what
        is that to you and to Me? My time</JESUS> [to act and to be revealed] <JESUS>has
        not yet come.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "His mother said to the servants, \u201CWhatever He says to you, do
        it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now there were six stone waterpots set there for the Jewish custom
        of purification (ceremonial washing), containing twenty or thirty gallons
        each. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Jesus said to the servants, <JESUS>\u201CFill the waterpots with
        water.\u201D</JESUS> So they filled them up to the brim. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CDraw </JESUS>some out now and
        take it to the headwaiter [of the banquet].\u201D So they took it to him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And when the headwaiter tasted the water which had turned into wine,
        not knowing where it came from (though the servants who had drawn the water
        knew) he called the bridegroom, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and said to him, \u201CEveryone else serves his best wine first,
        and when people have drunk freely, then he serves that which is not so good;
        but you have kept back the good wine until now.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "This, the first of His signs (attesting miracles), Jesus did in Cana
        of Galilee, and revealed His glory [displaying His deity and His great power
        openly], and His disciples believed [confidently] in Him [as the Messiah\u2014they
        adhered to, trusted in, and relied on Him].  "
      comments: []
    - name: "12: First Passover\u2014Cleansing the Temple"
      title: "First Passover\u2014Cleansing the Temple"
      number: 12
      content: 'After this He went down to Capernaum, He and His mother and brothers
        and His disciples; and they stayed there a few days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now the Passover of the Jews was approaching, so Jesus went up to
        Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And in the temple [enclosure] He found the people who were selling
        oxen and sheep and doves, and the money changers sitting at their tables. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He made a whip of cords, and drove them all out of the temple, with
        the sheep and the oxen; and He scattered the coins of the money changers
        and overturned their tables; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "then to those who sold the doves He said, <JESUS>\u201CTake these
        things away! Stop making My Father\u2019s house a place of commerce!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "His disciples remembered that it is written [in the Scriptures],
        \u201CZeal (love, concern) for Your house [and its honor] will consume Me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the Jews retorted, \u201CWhat sign (attesting miracle) can You
        show us as [proof of] your authority for doing these things?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Jesus answered them, <JESUS>\u201CDestroy this temple, and in three
        days I will raise it up.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then the Jews replied, \u201CIt took forty-six years to build this
        temple, and You will raise it up in three days?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But He was speaking of the temple which was His body. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So when He had risen from the dead, His disciples remembered what
        He had said. And they believed and trusted in and relied on the Scripture
        and the words that Jesus had spoken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now when He was in Jerusalem at the Passover feast, many believed
        in His name [identifying themselves with Him] after seeing His signs (attesting
        miracles) which He was doing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But Jesus, for His part, did not entrust Himself to them, because
        He knew all people [and understood the superficiality and fickleness of human
        nature], '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "and He did not need anyone to testify concerning man [and human nature],
        for He Himself knew what was in man [in their hearts\u2014in the very core
        of their being]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The New Birth'
      title: The New Birth
      number: 1
      content: '  Now there was a certain man among the Pharisees named Nicodemus,
        a ruler (member of the Sanhedrin) among the Jews, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "who came to Jesus at night and said to Him, \u201CRabbi (Teacher),
        we know [without any doubt] that You have come from God as a teacher; for
        no one can do these signs [these wonders, these attesting miracles] that
        You do unless God is with him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Jesus answered him, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly
        say to you, unless a person is born again [reborn from above\u2014spiritually
        transformed, renewed, sanctified], <JESUS>he cannot</JESUS> [ever] <JESUS>see
        </JESUS>and experience the kingdom of God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Nicodemus said to Him, \u201CHow can a man be born when he is old?
        He cannot enter his mother\u2019s womb a second time and be born, can he?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly
        say to you, unless one is born of water and the Spirit he cannot [ever] <JESUS>enter
        the kingdom of God.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<JESUS>That which is born of the flesh is flesh</JESUS> [the physical
        is merely physical], <JESUS>and that which is born of the Spirit is spirit.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>Do not be surprised that I have told you, \u2018You must be
        born again</JESUS> [reborn from above\u2014spiritually transformed, renewed,
        sanctified].\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>The wind blows where it wishes and you hear its sound, but
        you do not know where it is coming from and where it is going; so it is with
        everyone who is born of the Spirit.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Nicodemus said to Him, \u201CHow can these things be possible?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CYou are the</JESUS> [great and well-known]
        <JESUS>teacher of Israel, and yet you do not know </JESUS>nor understand
        these things [from Scripture]? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, we speak
        only of what we [absolutely] <JESUS>know and testify about what we have</JESUS>
        [actually] <JESUS>seen</JESUS> [as eyewitnesses]; <JESUS>and</JESUS> [still]
        <JESUS>you</JESUS> [reject our evidence and] <JESUS>do not accept our testimony.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>If I told you earthly things</JESUS> [that is, things that
        happen right here on earth] <JESUS>and you do not believe, how will you believe
        </JESUS>and trust Me if I tell you heavenly things?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>No one has gone up into heaven, but there is One who came
        down from heaven, the Son of Man</JESUS> [Himself\u2014whose home is in heaven]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>Just as Moses lifted up the</JESUS> [bronze] <JESUS>serpent
        in the desert</JESUS> [on a pole], <JESUS>so must the Son of Man be lifted
        up</JESUS> [on the cross], '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>so that whoever believes will in Him have eternal life</JESUS>
        [after physical death, and will actually live forever].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CFor God so</JESUS> [greatly] <JESUS>loved </JESUS>and
        dearly prized the world, that He [even] <JESUS>gave His</JESUS> [One and]
        <JESUS>only begotten Son, so that whoever believes </JESUS>and trusts in
        Him [as Savior] <JESUS>shall not perish, but have eternal life.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>For God did not send the Son into the world to judge </JESUS>and
        condemn the world [that is, to initiate the final judgment of the world],
        <JESUS>but that the world might be saved through Him.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '<JESUS>Whoever believes </JESUS>and has decided to trust in Him [as
        personal Savior and Lord] <JESUS>is not judged</JESUS> [for this one, there
        is no judgment, no rejection, no condemnation]; <JESUS>but the one who does
        not believe</JESUS> [and has decided to reject Him as personal Savior and
        Lord] <JESUS>is judged already</JESUS> [that one has been convicted and sentenced],
        <JESUS>because </JESUS><JESUS>he has not believed </JESUS>and trusted in
        the name of the [One and] <JESUS>only begotten Son of God</JESUS> [the One
        who is truly unique, the only One of His kind, the One who alone can save
        him]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>This is the judgment</JESUS> [that is, the cause for indictment,
        the test by which people are judged, the basis for the sentence]: <JESUS>the
        Light has come into the world, and people loved the </JESUS><JESUS>darkness
        rather than the Light, for their deeds were evil.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<JESUS>For every wrongdoer hates the Light, and does not come to
        the Light</JESUS> [but shrinks from it] <JESUS>for fear that his</JESUS>
        [sinful, worthless] <JESUS>activities will be exposed </JESUS>and condemned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "21: John\u2019s Last Testimony"
      title: "John\u2019s Last Testimony"
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>But whoever practices truth</JESUS> [and does what is right\u2014morally,
        ethically, spiritually] <JESUS>comes to the Light, so that his works may
        be plainly shown to be what they are\u2014accomplished in God</JESUS> [divinely
        prompted, done with God\u2019s help, in dependence on Him].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'After these things Jesus and His disciples went into the land of
        Judea, and there He spent time with them and baptized. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now John was also baptizing at Aenon near Salim, because there was
        an abundance of water there; and people were coming and were being baptized\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'for John had not yet been thrown into prison.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Therefore there arose a controversy between John\u2019s disciples
        and a Jew in regard to purification (ceremonial washing). "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So they came to John and said to him, \u201CRabbi (Teacher), the
        Man who was with you on the other side of the Jordan [at the Jordan River
        crossing]\u2014and to whom you have testified\u2014look, He is baptizing
        too, and everyone is going to Him!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "John replied, \u201CA man can receive nothing [he can claim nothing
        at all] unless it has been granted to him from heaven [for there is no other
        source than the sovereign will of God]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "You yourselves are my witnesses that I stated, \u2018I am not the
        Christ (the Messiah, the Anointed),\u2019 but, \u2018I have [only] been sent
        ahead of Him [as His appointed forerunner and messenger to announce and proclaim
        His coming].\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "He who has the bride is the bridegroom; but the friend of the bridegroom,
        who stands by and listens to him, rejoices greatly because of the bridegroom\u2019s
        voice. So this pleasure and joy of mine is now complete. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'He must increase [in prominence], but I must decrease.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CHe who comes from [heaven] above is above all others; he who
        is of the earth is from the earth and speaks [about things] of the earth
        [his viewpoint and experience are earthly]. He who comes from heaven is above
        all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'What He has [actually] seen and heard, of that He testifies; and
        yet no one accepts His testimony [as true]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Whoever receives His testimony has set his seal [of approval] to
        this: God is true [and he knows that God cannot lie]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "For He whom God has sent speaks the words of God [proclaiming the
        Father\u2019s own message]; for God gives the [gift of the] Spirit without
        measure [generously and boundlessly]! "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The Father loves the Son and has given and entrusted all things into
        His hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "He who believes and trusts in the Son and accepts Him [as Savior]
        has eternal life [that is, already possesses it]; but he who does not believe
        the Son and chooses to reject Him, [disobeying Him and denying Him as Savior]
        will not see [eternal] life, but [instead] the wrath of God hangs over him
        continually.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Goes to Galilee'
      title: Jesus Goes to Galilee
      number: 1
      content: '  So when the Lord learned that the Pharisees had been told that
        Jesus was making and baptizing more disciples than John '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '(although Jesus Himself was not baptizing, but His disciples were), '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He left Judea and returned again to Galilee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now He had to go through Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So He arrived at a Samaritan town called Sychar, near the tract of
        land that Jacob gave to his son Joseph; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: The Samaritan Woman'
      title: The Samaritan Woman
      number: 6
      content: "and Jacob\u2019s well was there. So Jesus, tired as He was from His
        journey, sat down by the well. It was then about the sixth hour (noon).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then a woman from Samaria came to draw water. Jesus said to her,
        <JESUS>\u201CGive Me a drink\u201D\u2014</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For His disciples had gone off into the city to buy food\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The Samaritan woman asked Him, \u201CHow is it that You, being a
        Jew, ask me, a Samaritan woman, for a drink?\u201D (For Jews have nothing
        to do with Samaritans.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus answered her, <JESUS>\u201CIf you knew</JESUS> [about] <JESUS>God\u2019s
        gift</JESUS> [of eternal life], <JESUS>and who it is who says, \u2018Give
        Me a drink,\u2019 you would have asked Him</JESUS> [instead], <JESUS>and
        He would have given you living water (eternal life).\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "She said to Him, \u201CSir, You have nothing to draw with [no bucket
        and rope] and the well is deep. Where then do You get that living water? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Are You greater than our father Jacob, who gave us the well, and
        who used to drink from it himself, and his sons and his cattle also?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Jesus answered her, <JESUS>\u201CEveryone who drinks this water will
        be thirsty again.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>But whoever drinks the water that I give him will never be
        thirsty again. But the water that I give him will become in him a spring
        of water</JESUS> [satisfying his thirst for God] <JESUS>welling up</JESUS>
        [continually flowing, bubbling within him] <JESUS>to eternal life.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The woman said to Him, \u201CSir, give me this water, so that I will
        not get thirsty nor [have to continually] come all the way here to draw.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "At this, Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CGo, call your husband and come
        back.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The woman answered, \u201CI do not have a husband.\u201D Jesus said
        to her, <JESUS>\u201CYou have correctly said, \u2018I do not have a husband\u2019;</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>for you have had five husbands, and the man you are now living
        with is not your </JESUS><JESUS>husband. You have said this truthfully.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The woman said to Him, \u201CSir, I see that You are a prophet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Our fathers worshiped on this mountain, but you Jews say that the
        place where one ought to worship is in Jerusalem [at the temple].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CWoman, believe Me, a time is coming</JESUS>
        [when God\u2019s kingdom comes] <JESUS>when you will worship the Father neither
        on this mountain nor in Jerusalem.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '<JESUS>You</JESUS> [Samaritans] <JESUS>do not know what you worship;
        we</JESUS> [Jews] <JESUS>do know what we worship, for salvation is from the
        Jews.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '<JESUS>But a time is coming and is already here when the true worshipers
        will worship the Father in spirit</JESUS> [from the heart, the inner self]
        <JESUS>and in truth; for the Father seeks such people to be His worshipers.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>God is spirit</JESUS> [the Source of life, yet invisible to
        mankind], <JESUS>and those who worship Him must worship in spirit and truth.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The woman said to Him, \u201CI know that Messiah is coming (He who
        is called Christ\u2014the Anointed); when that One comes, He will tell us
        everything [we need to know].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Jesus said to her, <JESUS>\u201CI who speak to you, am </JESUS>He
        (the Messiah).\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Just then His disciples came, and they were surprised to find Him
        talking with a woman. However, no one said, \u201CWhat are You asking about?\u201D
        or, \u201CWhy are You talking to her?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then the woman left her water jar, and went into the city and began
        telling the people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CCome, see a man who told me all the things that I have done!
        Can this be the Christ (the Messiah, the Anointed)?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So the people left the city and were coming to Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Meanwhile, the disciples were urging Jesus [to have a meal], saying,
        \u201CRabbi (Teacher), eat.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "But He told them, <JESUS>\u201CI have food to eat that you do not
        know about.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So the disciples said to one another, \u201CHas anyone brought Him
        something to eat?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CMy food is to do the will of Him
        who sent Me and to completely finish His work.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>Do you not say, \u2018It is still four months until the harvest
        comes?\u2019 Look, I say to you, raise your eyes and look at the fields </JESUS>and
        see, they are white for harvest.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: '<JESUS>Already the reaper is receiving </JESUS>his wages and he is
        gathering fruit for eternal life; so that he who plants and he who reaps
        may rejoice together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "<JESUS>For in this </JESUS>case the saying is true, \u2018One [person]
        <JESUS>sows and another reaps.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: The Samaritans'
      title: The Samaritans
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>I sent you to reap</JESUS> [a crop] <JESUS>for which you have
        not worked. Others have worked and you have been privileged to reap the results
        of their work.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Now many Samaritans from that city believed in Him and trusted Him
        [as Savior] because of what the woman said when she testified, \u201CHe told
        me all the things that I have done.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'So when the Samaritans came to Jesus, they asked Him to remain with
        them; and He stayed there two days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Many more believed in Him [with a deep, abiding trust] because of
        His word [His personal message to them]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "and they told the woman, \u201CWe no longer believe just because
        of what you said; for [now] we have heard Him for ourselves and know [with
        confident assurance] that this One is truly the Savior of [all] the world.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'After the two days He went on from there into Galilee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'For Jesus Himself declared that a prophet has no honor in his own
        country. '
      comments: []
    - name: "45: Healing a Nobleman\u2019s Son"
      title: "Healing a Nobleman\u2019s Son"
      number: 45
      content: 'So when He arrived in Galilee, the Galileans welcomed Him, since
        they had seen all the things that He did in Jerusalem at the feast; for they
        too came to the feast.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'So Jesus came again to Cana of Galilee, where He had turned the water
        into wine. And there was a certain royal official whose son was sick in Capernaum. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Having heard that Jesus had come back from Judea to Galilee, he went
        to meet Him and began asking Him to come down and heal his son; for he was
        at the point of death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Then Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CUnless you</JESUS> [people]
        <JESUS>see</JESUS> [miraculous] <JESUS>signs and wonders, you</JESUS> [simply]
        <JESUS>will not believe.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "The royal official pleaded with Him, \u201CSir, do come down [at
        once] before my child dies!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CGo; your son lives!\u201D</JESUS>
        The man believed what Jesus said to him and started home. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'As he was already going down [the road], his servants met him and
        reported that his son was living [and was healthy]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "So he asked them at what time he began to get better. They said,
        \u201CYesterday during the seventh hour (1 p.m.) the fever left him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "Then the father realized that it was at that very hour when Jesus
        had said to him, <JESUS>\u201CYour son lives\u201D;</JESUS> and he and his
        entire household believed and confidently trusted [in Him as Savior]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: This is the second sign (attesting miracle) that Jesus performed [in
        Cana] after He had come from Judea to Galilee [revealing that He is the Messiah].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Healing at Bethesda'
      title: The Healing at Bethesda
      number: 1
      content: '  Later on there was a Jewish feast (festival), and Jesus went up
        to Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now in Jerusalem, near the Sheep Gate, there is a pool, which is
        called in Hebrew (Jewish Aramaic) Bethesda, having five porticoes (alcoves,
        colonnades). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In these porticoes lay a great number of people who were sick, blind,
        lame, withered, [waiting for the stirring of the water; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'for an angel of the Lord went down into the pool at appointed seasons
        and stirred up the water; the first one to go in after the water was stirred
        was healed of his disease.]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'There was a certain man there who had been ill for thirty-eight years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When Jesus noticed him lying there [helpless], knowing that he had
        been in that condition a long time, He said to him, <JESUS>\u201CDo you want
        to get well?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The invalid answered, \u201CSir, I have no one to put me in the pool
        when the water is stirred up, and while I am coming [to get into it myself],
        someone else steps down ahead of me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CGet up; pick up your pallet and walk.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Immediately the man was healed and recovered his strength, and picked
        up his pallet and walked.  Now that day was the Sabbath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So the Jews kept saying to the man who had been healed, \u201CIt
        is the Sabbath, and you are not permitted to pick up your pallet [because
        it is unlawful].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He answered them, \u201CThe Man who healed me and gave me back my
        strength was the One who said to me, <JESUS>\u2018Pick up your pallet and
        walk.\u2019\u2009\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They asked him, \u201CWho is the Man who told you, <JESUS>\u2018Pick
        up </JESUS>your pallet and walk\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now the man who had been healed did not know who it was, for Jesus
        had slipped away [unnoticed] since there was a crowd in that place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Afterward, Jesus found him in the temple and said to him, <JESUS>\u201CSee,
        you are well! Stop sinning or something worse may happen to you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The man went away and told the Jews that it was Jesus who had made
        him well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For this reason the Jews began to persecute Jesus continually because
        He was doing these things on the Sabbath. '
      comments: []
    - name: "17: Jesus\u2019 Equality with God"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Equality with God"
      number: 17
      content: "But Jesus answered them, <JESUS>\u201CMy Father has been working
        until now</JESUS> [He has never ceased working], <JESUS>and I too am working.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'This made the Jews more determined than ever to kill Him, for not
        only was He breaking the Sabbath [from their viewpoint], but He was also
        calling God His own Father, making Himself equal with God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So Jesus answered them by saying, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and
        most solemnly say to you, the Son <JESUS>can do nothing of Himself</JESUS>
        [of His own accord], <JESUS>unless it is something He sees the Father doing;
        for whatever things the Father does, the Son</JESUS> [in His turn] <JESUS>also
        does in the same way.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<JESUS>For the Father </JESUS>dearly loves the Son and shows Him
        everything that He Himself is doing; and the Father will show Him greater
        works than these, so that you will be filled with wonder.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '<JESUS>Just as the Father raises the dead and gives them life</JESUS>
        [and allows them to live on], <JESUS>even so the Son also gives life to whom
        He wishes.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '<JESUS>For the Father judges no one, but has given all judgment</JESUS>
        [that is, the prerogative of judging] <JESUS>to the Son</JESUS> [placing
        it entirely into His hands], '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '<JESUS>so that all will give honor (reverence, homage) to the Son
        just as they give honor to the Father.</JESUS> [In fact] <JESUS>the one who
        does not honor the Son does not honor the Father who has sent Him.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Two Resurrections'
      title: Two Resurrections
      number: 24
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you,
        the person who hears My word [the one who heeds My message], <JESUS>and believes
        </JESUS>and trusts in Him who sent Me, has (possesses now) eternal life [that
        is, eternal life actually begins\u2014the believer is transformed], <JESUS>and
        does not come into judgment </JESUS>and condemnation, but has passed [over]
        <JESUS>from death into life.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  <JESUS>I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, a time
        is coming and is [here] <JESUS>now, when the dead will hear the voice of
        the Son of God, and those who hear it will live.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>For just as the Father has life in Himself</JESUS> [and is
        self-existent], <JESUS>even so He has given to the Son to have life in Himself</JESUS>
        [and be self-existent]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>And He has given Him authority to execute judgment, because
        He is a Son of Man</JESUS> [sinless humanity, qualifying Him to sit in judgment
        over mankind]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '<JESUS>Do not be surprised at this; for a time is coming when all
        those who are in the tombs will hear His voice,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>and they will come out\u2014those who did good things</JESUS>
        [will come out] <JESUS>to a resurrection of</JESUS> [new] <JESUS>life, but
        those who did evil things</JESUS> [will come out] <JESUS>to a resurrection
        of judgment</JESUS> [that is, to be sentenced].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI can do nothing on my own initiative </JESUS>or authority.
        Just as I hear, I judge; and My judgment is just (fair, righteous, unbiased),
        because I do not seek My own will, but only the will of Him who sent Me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CIf I </JESUS>alone testify about Myself, My testimony
        is not     <JESUS>valid.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: Testimony of John'
      title: Testimony of John
      number: 32
      content: '<JESUS>There is another</JESUS> [My Father] <JESUS>who testifies
        about Me, and I know</JESUS> [without any doubt] <JESUS>that His testimony
        on My behalf is true </JESUS>and valid.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '  <JESUS>You have sent</JESUS> [an inquiry] <JESUS>to </JESUS><JESUS>John</JESUS>
        [the Baptist] <JESUS>and he has testified</JESUS> [as an eyewitness] <JESUS>to
        the truth.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '<JESUS>But the testimony I receive is not from man</JESUS> [a merely
        human witness]; <JESUS>but I say these things so that you may be saved</JESUS>
        [that is, have eternal life]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: Testimony of Works'
      title: Testimony of Works
      number: 35
      content: '<JESUS>John was the lamp that kept on burning and shining</JESUS>
        [to show you the way], <JESUS>and you were willing for a while to rejoice
        in his light.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: Testimony of the Father'
      title: Testimony of the Father
      number: 36
      content: "  <JESUS>But the testimony which I have is far greater than </JESUS>the
        testimony of John; for the works that the Father has given Me to finish\u2014the
        very same works [that is, the miracles and proofs of My deity] <JESUS>that
        I am</JESUS> [now] <JESUS>doing\u2014testify about Me,</JESUS> [by providing
        evidence] <JESUS>that the Father has sent Me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "  <JESUS>And the Father who sent Me has Himself testified about Me.
        You have never heard His voice nor seen His form</JESUS> [His majesty and
        greatness\u2014what He is like]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: Testimony of the Scripture'
      title: Testimony of the Scripture
      number: 38
      content: '<JESUS>You do not have His word (Scripture) abiding in you</JESUS>
        [actually living in your hearts and minds], <JESUS>because you do not believe
        in Him whom He has sent.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: '    <JESUS>You search </JESUS>and keep on searching and examining
        the Scriptures because you think that in them you have eternal life; and
        yet it is those [very Scriptures] <JESUS>that testify about Me;</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: '<JESUS>and still you are unwilling to come to Me so that you may
        have life.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: '<JESUS>I do not receive glory </JESUS>and approval from men;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: '<JESUS>but I know you </JESUS>and recognize that you do not have
        the love of God in yourselves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "<JESUS>I have come in My Father\u2019s name </JESUS>and with His
        power, and you do not receive Me [because your minds are closed]; <JESUS>but
        if another comes in his own name </JESUS>and with no authority or power except
        his own, you will receive him and give your approval to an imposter.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: '<JESUS>How can you believe</JESUS> [in Me], <JESUS>when you</JESUS>
        [seek and] <JESUS>receive glory </JESUS>and approval from one another, and
        yet you do not seek the glory and approval which comes from the one and only
        God?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: '<JESUS>Do not think that I</JESUS> [am the One who] <JESUS>will accuse
        you before the Father. There</JESUS> [already] <JESUS>is one who accuses
        you: Moses,</JESUS> [the very one] <JESUS>in whom you have placed your hope</JESUS>
        [for salvation]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: '<JESUS>For if you believed </JESUS>and relied on [the Scriptures
        written by] <JESUS>Moses, you would believe Me, for he wrote about Me</JESUS>
        [personally]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "<JESUS>But if you do not believe his writings, how will you believe
        My words?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Five Thousand Fed'
      title: Five Thousand Fed
      number: 1
      content: '  After this, Jesus went to the other side of the Sea of Galilee
        (or Sea of Tiberias). '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'A large crowd was following Him because they had seen the signs (attesting
        miracles) which He continually performed on those who were sick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Jesus went up on the mountainside and sat down there with His
        disciples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now the Passover, the feast of the Jews, was approaching. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Jesus looked up and saw that a large crowd was coming toward Him,
        and He said to Philip, <JESUS>\u201CWhere will we buy bread for these </JESUS>people
        to eat?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But He said this to test Philip, because He knew what He was about
        to do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Philip answered, \u201CTwo hundred denarii (200 days\u2019 wages)
        worth of bread is not enough for each one to receive even a little.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "One of His disciples, Andrew, Simon Peter\u2019s brother, said to
        Him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThere is a little boy here who has five barley loaves and two
        fish; but what are these for so many people?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CHave the people sit down</JESUS> [to eat].\u201D
        Now [the ground] there was [covered with] an abundance of grass, so the men
        sat down, about 5,000 in number. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Jesus took the loaves, and when He had given thanks, He distributed
        them to those who were seated; the same also with the fish, as much as they
        wanted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When they had eaten enough, He said to His disciples, <JESUS>\u201CGather
        up the leftover pieces so that nothing will be lost.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So they gathered them up, and they filled twelve large baskets with
        pieces from the five barley loaves which were left over by those who had
        eaten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Jesus Walks on the Water'
      title: Jesus Walks on the Water
      number: 14
      content: "When the people saw the sign (attesting miracle) that He had done,
        they began saying, \u201CThis is without a doubt the promised Prophet who
        is to come into the world!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Jesus, knowing that they were going to come and take Him by
        force to make Him king, withdrew again to the mountainside by Himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When evening came, His disciples went down to the sea, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and they got into a boat and started to cross the sea to Capernaum.
        It was already dark, and Jesus had still not come [back] to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The sea was getting rough and rising high because a strong wind was
        blowing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then, when they had rowed three or four miles [and were near the
        center of the sea], they saw Jesus walking on the sea and approaching the
        boat; and they were [terribly] frightened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CIt is I (I AM); do not be afraid.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then they were willing to take Him on board the boat, and immediately
        the boat reached the [shore of the] land to which they were going.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The next day the crowd that stood on the other side of the sea realized
        that there had been only one small boat there, and that Jesus had not boarded
        the boat with His disciples, but that His disciples had gone away alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '[Now some] other small boats from Tiberias had come in near the place
        where they ate the bread after the Lord had given thanks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So when the crowd saw that neither Jesus nor His disciples were there,
        they boarded the small boats themselves and came to Capernaum looking for
        Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Words to the People'
      title: Words to the People
      number: 25
      content: "And when they found Him on the other side of the sea, they asked
        Him, \u201CRabbi, when did You get here?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly
        say to you, you have been searching for Me, not because you saw the signs
        (attesting miracles), but because you ate the loaves and were filled.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>Do not work for food that perishes, but for food that endures</JESUS>
        [and leads] <JESUS>to eternal life, which the Son of Man will give you; for
        God the Father has authorized Him </JESUS>and put His seal on Him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then they asked Him, \u201CWhat are we to do, so that we may habitually
        be doing the works of God?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CThis is the work of God: that you believe</JESUS>
        [adhere to, trust in, rely on, and have faith] <JESUS>in the One whom He
        has sent.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So they said to Him, \u201CWhat sign (attesting miracle) will You
        do that we may see it and believe You? What [supernatural] work will You
        do [as proof]? "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Our fathers ate the manna in the wilderness; as it is written [in
        Scripture], \u2018He gave them bread out of heaven to eat.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most
        solemnly say to you, it is not Moses who has given you the bread out of heaven,
        but it is My Father who gives you the true <JESUS>bread out of heaven.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>For the Bread of God is He who comes down out of heaven, and
        gives life to the world.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then they said to Him, \u201CLord, always give us this bread.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Jesus replied to them, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>I am the Bread
        of Life. The one who comes to Me will never be hungry, and the one who believes
        in Me</JESUS> [as Savior] <JESUS>will never be thirsty</JESUS> [for that
        one will be sustained spiritually]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: '<JESUS>But as I told you, you have seen Me and still you do not believe.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: '<JESUS>All that My Father gives Me will come to Me; and the one who
        comes to Me I will most certainly not cast out</JESUS> [I will never, never
        reject anyone who follows Me]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '<JESUS>For I have come down from heaven, not to do My own will, but
        to do the will of Him who sent Me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: '<JESUS>This is the will of Him who sent Me, that of all that He has
        given Me I lose nothing, but that I</JESUS> [give new life and] <JESUS>raise
        it up at the last day.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: Words to the Jews'
      title: Words to the Jews
      number: 40
      content: "<JESUS>For this is My Father\u2019s will </JESUS>and purpose, that
        everyone who sees the Son and believes in Him [as Savior] <JESUS>will have
        eternal life, and I will raise him up</JESUS> [from the dead] <JESUS>on the
        last day.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Now the Jews murmured and found fault with Him because He said, <JESUS>\u201CI
        am the Bread that came down out of heaven.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "They kept saying, \u201CIs this not Jesus, the son of Joseph, whose
        father and mother we know? How does He now [have the arrogance to] say, <JESUS>\u2018I
        have come down out of heaven\u2019?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "So Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CStop murmuring among yourselves.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: '<JESUS>No one can come to Me unless the Father who sent Me draws
        him</JESUS> [giving him the desire to come to Me]; <JESUS>and I will raise
        him up</JESUS> [from the dead] <JESUS>on the last day.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "<JESUS>It is written in the prophets, \u2018A</JESUS>nd they will
        all be taught of God.\u2019 Everyone who has listened to and learned from
        the Father, comes to Me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: '<JESUS>Not that anyone has seen the Father, except He</JESUS> [who
        was with the Father and] <JESUS>who is from God; He</JESUS> [alone] <JESUS>has
        seen the Father.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "<JESUS>I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, he who
        believes [in Me as Savior\u2014whoever adheres to, trusts in, relies on,
        and has faith in Me\u2014already] <JESUS>has eternal life</JESUS> [that is,
        now possesses it]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: '<JESUS>I am the Bread of Life</JESUS> [the Living Bread which gives
        and sustains life]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: '<JESUS>Your fathers ate the manna in the wilderness, and they died.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: '<JESUS>This is the Bread that comes down out of heaven, so that one
        may eat of it and not die.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "<JESUS>I am the Living Bread that came down out of heaven. If anyone
        eats of this Bread</JESUS> [believes in Me, accepts Me as Savior], <JESUS>he
        will live forever. And the Bread that I will give for the life of the world
        is My flesh (body).\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "Then the Jews began to argue with one another, saying, \u201CHow
        can this man give us His flesh to eat?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "And Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most
        solemnly say to you, unless you eat the flesh of the Son of Man and drink
        His blood [unless you believe in Me as Savior and believe in the saving power
        of My blood which will be shed for you], <JESUS>you do not have life in yourselves.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: '<JESUS>The one who eats My flesh and drinks My blood</JESUS> [believes
        in Me, accepts Me as Savior] <JESUS>has eternal life</JESUS> [that is, now
        possesses it], <JESUS>and I will raise him up</JESUS> [from the dead] <JESUS>on
        the last day.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: '<JESUS>For My flesh is true</JESUS> [spiritual] <JESUS>food, and
        My blood is true</JESUS> [spiritual] <JESUS>drink.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: '<JESUS>He who eats My flesh and drinks My blood</JESUS> [believes
        in Me, accepts Me as Savior] <JESUS>remains in Me, and I</JESUS> [in the
        same way remain] <JESUS>in him.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: '<JESUS>Just as the living Father sent Me, and I live because of the
        Father, even so the one who feeds on Me</JESUS> [believes in Me, accepts
        Me as Savior] <JESUS>will also live because of Me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: Words to the Disciples'
      title: Words to the Disciples
      number: 58
      content: "<JESUS>This is the Bread which came down out of heaven. It is not
        like</JESUS> [the manna that] <JESUS>our fathers ate and they</JESUS> [eventually]
        <JESUS>died; the one who eats this Bread</JESUS> [believes in Me, accepts
        Me as Savior] <JESUS>will live forever.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'He said these things in a synagogue while He was teaching in Capernaum.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "When many of His disciples heard this, they said, \u201CThis is a
        difficult and harsh and offensive statement. Who can [be expected to] listen
        to it?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "But Jesus, aware that His disciples were complaining about it, asked
        them, <JESUS>\u201CDoes this cause you to stumble </JESUS>and take offense?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: '<JESUS>What</JESUS> then [will you think] <JESUS>if you see the Son
        of Man ascending to</JESUS> [the realm] <JESUS>where He was before?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: '<JESUS>It is the Spirit who gives life; the flesh conveys no benefit</JESUS>
        [it is of no account]. <JESUS>The words I have spoken to you are spirit and
        life</JESUS> [providing eternal life]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: "<JESUS>But</JESUS> [still] <JESUS>there are some of you who do not
        believe </JESUS>and have faith.\u201D For Jesus knew from the beginning who
        did not believe, and who would betray Him. "
      comments: []
    - name: "65: Peter\u2019s Confession of Faith"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Confession of Faith"
      number: 65
      content: "And He was saying, <JESUS>\u201CThis is the reason why I have told
        you that no one can come to Me unless it has been granted him</JESUS> [that
        is, unless he is enabled to do so] <JESUS>by the Father.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'As a result of this many of His disciples abandoned Him, and no longer
        walked with Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: "So Jesus said to the twelve [disciples], <JESUS>\u201CYou do not
        want to leave too, do you?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: "Simon Peter answered, \u201CLord, to whom shall we go? You [alone]
        have the words of eternal life [you are our only hope]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: "We have believed and confidently trusted, and [even more] we have
        come to know [by personal observation and experience] that You are the Holy
        One of God [the Christ, the Son of the living God].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: "Jesus answered them, <JESUS>\u201CDid I not choose you, the twelve</JESUS>
        [disciples]? <JESUS>And yet one of you is a devil (ally of Satan).\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: Now He was speaking of Judas, the son of Simon Iscariot; for he, one
        of the twelve [disciples], was about to betray Him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Teaches at the Feast'
      title: Jesus Teaches at the Feast
      number: 1
      content: '  After this, Jesus walked [from place to place] in Galilee, for
        He would not walk in Judea because the Jews were seeking to kill Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now the Jewish Feast of Tabernacles (Booths) was approaching. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So His brothers said to Him, \u201CLeave here and go to Judea, so
        that Your disciples [there] may also see the works that You do. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "No one does anything in secret when he wants to be known publicly.
        If You [must] do these things, show Yourself openly to the world and make
        Yourself known!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For not even His brothers believed in Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CMy time has not yet come; but
        any time is right for you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '<JESUS>The world cannot hate you</JESUS> [since you are part of it],
        <JESUS>but it does hate Me because I denounce it </JESUS>and testify that
        its deeds are evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>Go up to the feast yourselves. I am not going up to this feast
        because My time has not yet fully come.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Having said these things to them, He stayed behind in Galilee.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But [afterward], when His brothers had gone up to the feast, He went
        up too, not publicly [with a caravan], but quietly [because He did not want
        to be noticed]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So the Jews kept looking for Him at the feast and asking, \u201CWhere
        is He?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "There was a lot of whispered discussion and murmuring among the crowds
        about Him. Some were saying, \u201CHe is a good man\u201D; others said, \u201CNo,
        on the contrary, He misleads the people [giving them false ideas].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Yet no one was speaking out openly and freely about Him for fear
        of [the leaders of] the Jews.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When the feast was already half over, Jesus went up into the temple
        [court] and began to teach. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the Jews were perplexed. They said, \u201CHow did this man become
        learned [so versed in the Scriptures and theology] without formal training?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Jesus answered them by saying, <JESUS>\u201CMy teaching is not My
        own, but His who sent Me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>If anyone is willing to do His will, he will know whether
        the teaching is of God or whether I speak on My own accord </JESUS>and by
        My own authority.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '<JESUS>He who speaks on his own accord seeks glory </JESUS>and honor
        for himself. But He who seeks the glory and the honor of the One who sent
        Him, He is true, and there is no unrighteousness or deception in Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CDid not Moses give you the Law? And yet not one of
        you keeps the Law. Why do you want to kill Me</JESUS> [for not keeping it]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The crowd answered, \u201CYou have a demon [You are out of Your mind]!
        Who wants to kill You?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CI did one </JESUS><JESUS>work, and you
        are all astounded.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>For this reason Moses has given you</JESUS> [God\u2019s law
        regarding] <JESUS>circumcision </JESUS>(not that it originated with Moses,
        but with the patriarchs) and you circumcise a man [even] <JESUS>on the Sabbath.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>If, to avoid breaking the Law of Moses, a man undergoes </JESUS><JESUS>circumcision
        on the Sabbath, why are you angry with Me for making a man\u2019s whole body
        well on the Sabbath?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>Do not judge by appearance</JESUS> [superficially and arrogantly],
        <JESUS>but judge fairly </JESUS>and righteously.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then some of the people of Jerusalem said, \u201CIs this not the
        Man they want to kill? "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Look, He is speaking publicly, and they say nothing to Him! Is it
        possible that the rulers really know that this is the Christ? '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But we know where this Man is from; whenever the Christ comes, no
        one will know where He is from.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Jesus called out as He taught in the temple, <JESUS>\u201CYou
        know Me and know where I am from; and I have not come on my own initiative</JESUS>
        [as self-appointed], <JESUS>but He who sent Me is true, and Him you do not
        know.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>I know Him Myself because I am from Him</JESUS> [I came from
        His very presence] <JESUS>and it was He</JESUS> [personally] <JESUS>who sent
        Me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So they were eager to arrest Him; but no one laid a hand on Him,
        because His time had not yet come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But many from the crowd believed in Him. And they kept saying, \u201CWhen
        the Christ comes, will He do more signs and exhibit more proofs than this
        Man?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The Pharisees heard the crowd muttering these things [under their
        breath] about Him, and the chief priests and Pharisees sent guards to arrest
        Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Therefore Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CFor a little while longer I am</JESUS>
        [still] <JESUS>with you, and then I go to Him who sent Me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "<JESUS>You will look for Me, and will not</JESUS> [be able to] <JESUS>find
        Me; and where I am, you cannot come.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then the Jews said among themselves, \u201CWhere does this Man intend
        to go that we will not find Him? Does He intend to go to the Dispersion [of
        Jews scattered and living] among the Greeks, and teach the Greeks? "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "What does this statement of His mean, <JESUS>\u2018You will look
        for Me, and will not</JESUS> [be able to] <JESUS>find Me; and where I am,
        you cannot come\u2019?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Now on the last and most important day of the feast, Jesus stood
        and called out [in a loud voice], <JESUS>\u201CIf anyone is thirsty, let
        him come to Me and drink!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>He who believes in Me</JESUS> [who adheres to, trusts in,
        and relies on Me], <JESUS>as the Scripture has said, \u2018From his innermost
        being will flow </JESUS>continually rivers of living water.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: Division of People over Jesus'
      title: Division of People over Jesus
      number: 39
      content: 'But He was speaking of the [Holy] Spirit, whom those who believed
        in Him [as Savior] were to receive afterward. The Spirit had not yet been
        given, because Jesus was not yet glorified (raised to honor).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Listening to these words, some of the people said, \u201CThis is
        certainly the Prophet!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Others said, \u201CThis is the Christ (the Messiah, the Anointed)!\u201D
        But others said, \u201CSurely the Christ is not going to come out of Galilee,
        is He? "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Does the Scripture not say that the Christ comes from the descendants
        of David, and from Bethlehem, the village where David lived?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'So the crowd was divided because of Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Some of them wanted to arrest Him, but no one laid hands on Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "Then the guards went [back] to the chief priests and Pharisees, who
        asked them, \u201CWhy did you not bring Him [here with you]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "The guards replied, \u201CNever [at any time] has a man talked the
        way this Man talks!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Then the Pharisees said to them, \u201CHave you also been deluded
        and swept off your feet? "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Has any of the rulers or Pharisees believed in Him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "But this [ignorant, contemptible] crowd that does not know the Law
        is accursed and doomed!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Nicodemus (the one who came to Jesus before and was one of them)
        asked, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "\u201CDoes our Law convict someone without first giving him a hearing
        and finding out what he is [accused of] doing?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "They responded, \u201CAre you also from Galilee? Search [and read
        the Scriptures], and see [for yourself] that no prophet comes from Galilee!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: '[And everyone went to his own house.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Adulterous Woman'
      title: The Adulterous Woman
      number: 1
      content: '  But Jesus went to the Mount of Olives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Early in the morning He came back into the temple [court], and all
        the people were coming to Him. He sat down and began teaching them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now the scribes and Pharisees brought a woman who had been caught
        in adultery. They made her stand in the center of the court,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and they said to Him, \u201CTeacher, this woman has been caught in
        the very act of adultery. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now in the Law Moses commanded us to stone such women [to death].
        So what do You say [to do with her\u2014what is Your sentence]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They said this to test Him, hoping that they would have grounds for
        accusing Him. But Jesus stooped down and began writing on the ground with
        His finger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "However, when they persisted in questioning Him, He straightened
        up and said, <JESUS>\u201CHe who is without</JESUS> [any] <JESUS>sin among
        you, let him be the first to throw a stone at her.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then He stooped down again and started writing on the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They listened [to His reply], and they began to go out one by one,
        starting with the oldest ones, until He was left alone, with the woman [standing
        there before Him] in the center of the court.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Straightening up, Jesus said to her, <JESUS>\u201CWoman, where are
        they? Did no one condemn you?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Jesus Is the Light of the World'
      title: Jesus Is the Light of the World
      number: 11
      content: "She answered, \u201CNo one, Lord!\u201D And Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CI
        do not condemn you either. Go. From now on sin no more.\u201D</JESUS>]  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Once more Jesus addressed the crowd. He said, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>I
        am the Light of the world. He who follows Me will not walk in the darkness,
        but will have the Light of life.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the Pharisees told Him, \u201CYou are testifying on Your own
        behalf; Your testimony is not valid.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CEven if I do testify on My own behalf,
        My testimony is valid, because I know where I came from and where I am going;
        but you do not know where I come from or where I am going.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>You judge according to </JESUS><JESUS>human standards</JESUS>
        [just by what you see]. <JESUS>I do not judge anyone.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>But even if I do judge, My judgment is true </JESUS>and My
        decision is right; for I am not alone [in making it], <JESUS>but I and the
        Father who sent Me</JESUS> [make the same judgment]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>Even in your own law it is written that the testimony of two
        persons is true</JESUS> [valid and admissible]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>I am One</JESUS> [of the Two] <JESUS>who testifies about Myself,
        and My Father who sent Me testifies about Me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the Pharisees said to Him, \u201CWhere is this Father of Yours?\u201D
        Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CYou know neither Me nor My Father; if you knew
        Me, you would know My Father also.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Jesus said these things in the treasury, as He taught in the temple
        [courtyard]; and no one seized Him, because His time had not yet come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then He said again to them, <JESUS>\u201CI am going away, and you
        will look for Me, and you will die</JESUS> [unforgiven and condemned] <JESUS>in
        your sin. Where I am going, you cannot come.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So the Jews were asking [among themselves], \u201CWill He kill Himself?
        Is that why He says, <JESUS>\u2018Where I am going, you cannot come\u2019?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CYou are from below, I am from above;
        you are of this world, I am not of this world.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>That is why I told you that you will die</JESUS> [unforgiven
        and condemned] <JESUS>in your sins; for if you do not believe that I am </JESUS>the
        One [I claim to be], <JESUS>you will die in your sins.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So they said to Him, \u201CWho are You [anyway]?\u201D Jesus replied,
        <JESUS>\u201CWhat have I been saying to you from the beginning?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>I have many things to say and judge concerning you, but He
        who sent Me is true; and I say to the world</JESUS> [only] <JESUS>the things
        that I have heard from Him.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'They did not realize [or have the spiritual insight to understand]
        that He was speaking to them about the Father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CWhen you lift up the Son of Man</JESUS>
        [on the cross], <JESUS>you will know then</JESUS> [without any doubt] <JESUS>that
        I am </JESUS>He, and that I do nothing on My own authority, but I say these
        things just as My Father taught Me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>And He who sent Me is</JESUS> [always] <JESUS>with Me; He
        has not left Me alone, because I always do what pleases Him.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: The Truth Will Make You Free'
      title: The Truth Will Make You Free
      number: 30
      content: 'As He said these things, many believed in Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So Jesus was saying to the Jews who had believed Him, <JESUS>\u201CIf
        you abide in My word</JESUS> [continually obeying My teachings and living
        in accordance with them, then] <JESUS>you are truly My disciples.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>And you will know the truth</JESUS> [regarding salvation],
        <JESUS>and the truth will set you free</JESUS> [from the penalty of sin].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "They answered Him, \u201CWe are Abraham\u2019s descendants and have
        never been enslaved to anyone. What do You mean by saying, <JESUS>\u2018You
        will be set free\u2019?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly
        say to you, everyone who practices sin habitually is a slave of sin.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '<JESUS>Now the slave does not remain in a household forever; the
        son</JESUS> [of the master] <JESUS>does remain forever.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: '<JESUS>So if the Son makes you free, then you are unquestionably
        free.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "<JESUS>I know that you are Abraham\u2019s descendants; yet you plan
        to kill Me, because My word has no place</JESUS> [to grow] <JESUS>in you</JESUS>
        [and it makes no change in your heart]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>I tell the things that I have seen at My Father\u2019s side</JESUS>
        [in His very presence]; <JESUS>so you also do the things that you heard from
        your father.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "They answered, \u201CAbraham is our father.\u201D Jesus said to them,
        <JESUS>\u201CIf you are</JESUS> [truly] <JESUS>Abraham\u2019s children, then
        do the works of Abraham </JESUS>and follow his example.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: '<JESUS>But as it is, you want to kill Me, a Man who has told you
        the truth, which I heard from God. This is not the way Abraham acted.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "<JESUS>You are doing the works of your</JESUS> [own] <JESUS>father.\u201D</JESUS>
        They said to Him, \u201CWe are not illegitimate children; we have one [spiritual]
        Father: God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CIf God were your Father</JESUS>
        [but He is not], <JESUS>you would love </JESUS>and recognize Me, for I came
        from God [out of His very presence] <JESUS>and have arrived </JESUS>here.
        For I have not even come on My own initiative [as self-appointed], <JESUS>but
        He</JESUS> [is the One who] <JESUS>sent Me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: '<JESUS>Why do you misunderstand what I am saying? It is because</JESUS>
        [your spiritual ears are deaf and] <JESUS>you are unable to hear</JESUS>
        [the truth of] <JESUS>My word.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: '<JESUS>You are of </JESUS>your father the devil, and it is your will
        to practice the desires [which are characteristic] <JESUS>of your father.
        He was a murderer from the beginning, and does not stand in the truth because
        there is no truth in him. When he lies, he speaks what is natural to him,
        for he is a liar and the father of lies </JESUS>and half-truths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: '<JESUS>But because I speak the truth, you do not believe Me</JESUS>
        [and continue in your unbelief]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: '<JESUS>Which one of you</JESUS> [has proof and] <JESUS>convicts Me
        of sin? If I speak truth, why do you not believe Me?</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "<JESUS>Whoever is of God </JESUS>and belongs to Him hears [the truth
        of] <JESUS>God\u2019s words; for this reason you do not hear them: because
        you are not of God </JESUS>and you are not in fellowship with Him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "The Jews answered Him, \u201CAre we not right when we say You are
        a Samaritan and [that You] have a demon [and are under its power]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CI do not have a demon. On the contrary,
        I honor My Father, and you dishonor Me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: '<JESUS>However, I am not seeking glory for Myself. There is One who
        seeks</JESUS> [glory for Me] <JESUS>and judges</JESUS> [those who dishonor
        Me]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "<JESUS>I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, if anyone
        keeps My word [by living in accordance with My message] <JESUS>he will indeed
        never, ever see </JESUS>and experience <JESUS>death.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "The Jews said to Him, \u201CNow we know that You have a demon [and
        are under its power]. Abraham died, and also the prophets; yet You say, <JESUS>\u2018If
        anyone keeps My word, he will never, ever taste of death.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "Are You greater than our father Abraham, who died? The prophets died
        too! Whom do You make Yourself out to be?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CIf I glorify Myself, My glory is</JESUS>
        [worth] <JESUS>nothing. It is My Father who glorifies Me, of whom you say,
        \u2018He is our God.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: '<JESUS>Yet you do not know Him, but I know Him fully. If I said I
        did not know Him, I would be a liar like you. But I do know Him and keep
        His word.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "<JESUS>Your father Abraham</JESUS> [greatly] <JESUS>rejoiced to see
        My day (My incarnation). </JESUS><JESUS>He saw it and was delighted.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "Then the Jews said to Him, \u201CYou are not even fifty years old,
        and You [claim to] have seen Abraham?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly
        say to you, before Abraham was born, <JESUS>I Am.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: So they picked up stones to throw at Him, but Jesus concealed Himself
        and left the temple.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Healing the Man Born Blind'
      title: Healing the Man Born Blind
      number: 1
      content: '  While He was passing by, He noticed a man [who had been] blind
        from birth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "His disciples asked Him, \u201CRabbi (Teacher), who sinned, this
        man or his parents, that he would be born blind?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CNeither this man nor his parents sinned,
        but it was so that the works of God might be displayed </JESUS>and illustrated
        in him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>We must work the works of Him who sent Me while it is day;
        night is coming when no one can work.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>As long as I am in the world, I am the Light of the world</JESUS>
        [giving guidance through My word and works].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When He had said this, He spat on the ground and made mud with His
        saliva, and He spread the mud [like an ointment] on the man\u2019s eyes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And He said to him, <JESUS>\u201CGo, wash in the pool of </JESUS><JESUS>Siloam\u201D</JESUS>
        (which is translated, Sent). So he went away and washed, and came back seeing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So the neighbors, and those who used to know him as a beggar, said,
        \u201CIs not this the man who used to sit and beg?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Some said, \u201CIt is he.\u201D Still others said, \u201CNo, but
        he looks like him.\u201D But he kept saying, \u201CI am the man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So they said to him, \u201CHow were your eyes opened?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He replied, \u201CThe Man called Jesus made mud and smeared it on
        my eyes and told me, <JESUS>\u2018Go to Siloam and wash.\u2019</JESUS> So
        I went and washed, and I received my sight!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Controversy over the Man'
      title: Controversy over the Man
      number: 12
      content: "They asked him, \u201CWhere is He?\u201D He said, \u201CI do not
        know.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then they brought the man who was formerly blind to the Pharisees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now it was on a Sabbath day that Jesus made the mud and opened the
        man\u2019s eyes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So the Pharisees asked him again how he received his sight. And he
        said to them, \u201CHe smeared mud on my eyes, and I washed, and now I see.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then some of the Pharisees said, \u201CThis Man [Jesus] is not from
        God, because He does not keep the Sabbath.\u201D But others said, \u201CHow
        can a man who is a sinner (a non-observant Jew) do such signs and miracles?\u201D
        So there was a difference of opinion among them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Accordingly they said to the blind man again, \u201CWhat do you say
        about Him, since He opened your eyes?\u201D And he said, \u201C[It must be
        that] He is a prophet!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "However, the Jews did not believe that he had been blind and had
        received his sight until they called the man\u2019s parents. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They asked them, \u201CIs this your son, who you say was born blind?
        Then how does he now see?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "His parents answered, \u201CWe know that this is our son, and that
        he was born blind; "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "but as to how he now sees, we do not know; or who has opened his
        eyes, we do not know. Ask him [and stop asking us]; he is of age, he will
        speak for himself and give his own account of it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'His parents said this because they were afraid of [the leaders of]
        the Jews; for the Jews had already agreed that if anyone acknowledged Jesus
        to be the Christ, he would be put out of the synagogue (excommunicated). '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Because of this his parents said, \u201CHe is of age; ask him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So a second time they called the man who had been [born] blind, and
        said to him, \u201CGive God glory and praise [for your sight]! We know this
        Man [Jesus] is a sinner [separated from God].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then he answered, \u201CI do not know whether He is a sinner [separated
        from God]; but one thing I do know, that though I was blind, now I see.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So they said to him, \u201CWhat did He [actually] do to you? How
        did He open your eyes?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "He answered, \u201CI already told you and you did not listen. Why
        do you want to hear it again and again? Do you want to become His disciples,
        too?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And [at that remark] they stormed at him and jeered, \u201CYou are
        His disciple, but we are disciples of Moses! "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "We know [for certain] that God has spoken to Moses, but as for this
        Man, we do not know where He is from.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "The man replied, \u201CWell, this is astonishing! You do not know
        where He comes from, and yet He opened my eyes! "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'We know [according to your tradition] that God does not hear sinners;
        but if anyone fears God and does His will, He hears him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Since the beginning of time it has never been heard that anyone opened
        the eyes of a person born blind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "If this Man were not from God, He would not be able to do anything
        [like this because God would not hear His prayer].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: Jesus Affirms His Deity'
      title: Jesus Affirms His Deity
      number: 34
      content: "They answered him, \u201CYou were born entirely in sins [from head
        to foot], and you [presume to] teach us?\u201D Then they threw him out [of
        the synagogue].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Jesus heard that they had put him out [of the synagogue], and finding
        him, He asked, <JESUS>\u201CDo you believe in the Son of Man?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "He answered, \u201CWho is He, Sir? Tell me so that I may believe
        in Him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CYou have both seen Him, and</JESUS>
        [in fact] <JESUS>He is the one who is talking with you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And he said, \u201CLord, I believe [in You and Your word]!\u201D
        And he worshiped Him [with reverence and awe]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CI came into this world for judgment</JESUS>
        [to separate those who believe in Me from those who reject Me\u2014to declare
        judgment on those who choose to be separated from God], <JESUS>so that the
        sightless would see, and those who see would become blind.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Some Pharisees who were with Him heard these things and said to Him,
        \u201CAre we also blind?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CIf you were blind</JESUS> [to spiritual
        things], <JESUS>you would have no sin</JESUS> [and would not be blamed for
        your unbelief]; <JESUS>but since you claim to have</JESUS> [spiritual] <JESUS>sight,</JESUS>
        [you have no excuse so] <JESUS>your sin </JESUS>and guilt remain."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Parable of the Good Shepherd'
      title: Parable of the Good Shepherd
      number: 1
      content: "    <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you,
        he who does not enter by the door into the sheepfold, but climbs up from
        some other place [on the stone wall], <JESUS>that one is a thief and a robber.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '<JESUS>But he who enters by the door is the shepherd of the sheep</JESUS>
        [the protector and provider]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>The </JESUS><JESUS>doorkeeper opens</JESUS> [the gate] <JESUS>for
        this man, and the sheep hear his voice </JESUS>and pay attention to it. And
        [knowing that they listen] <JESUS>he calls his own sheep by name and leads
        them out</JESUS> [to pasture]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>When he has brought all his own </JESUS>sheep outside, he
        walks on ahead of them, and the sheep follow him because they know his voice
        and recognize his call.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>They will never follow a stranger, but will run away from
        him, because they do not know the voice of strangers.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Jesus used this figure of speech with them, but they did not understand
        what He was talking about.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Jesus said again, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly
        say to you, I am <JESUS>the Door for the sheep</JESUS> [leading to life]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>All who came before Me</JESUS> [as false messiahs and self-appointed
        leaders] <JESUS>are thieves and robbers, but the</JESUS> [true] <JESUS>sheep
        did not hear them.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '<JESUS>I am the Door; anyone who enters through Me will be saved</JESUS>
        [and will live forever], <JESUS>and will go in and out</JESUS> [freely],
        <JESUS>and find pasture (spiritual security).</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<JESUS>The thief comes only in order to steal and kill and destroy.
        I came that they may have life, and have it in abundance</JESUS> [to the
        full, till it overflows].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '    <JESUS>I am the Good Shepherd. The Good Shepherd </JESUS>   
        <JESUS>lays down His</JESUS> [own] <JESUS>life for the sheep.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>But the hired man</JESUS> [who merely serves for wages], <JESUS>who
        is neither the shepherd nor the owner of the sheep, when he sees the wolf
        coming, deserts the flock and runs away; and the wolf snatches the sheep
        and scatters </JESUS>them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '<JESUS>The </JESUS>man runs because he is a hired hand [who serves
        only for wages] <JESUS>and is not concerned about the</JESUS> [safety of
        the] <JESUS>sheep.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>I am the Good Shepherd, and I know</JESUS> [without any doubt
        those who are] <JESUS>My own and My own know Me</JESUS> [and have a deep,
        personal relationship with Me]\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>even as the Father knows Me and I know the Father\u2014and
        I lay down My</JESUS> [very own] <JESUS>life</JESUS> [sacrificing it] <JESUS>for
        </JESUS>the benefit of the sheep.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>I have </JESUS><JESUS>other sheep</JESUS> [beside these] <JESUS>that
        are not of this fold. I must bring those also, and they will listen to My
        voice </JESUS>and pay attention to My call, and they will become <JESUS>one
        flock with one Shepherd.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>For this reason the Father loves Me, because I lay down My</JESUS>
        [own] <JESUS>life so that I may take it back.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>No one takes it away from Me, but I lay it down voluntarily.
        I am authorized </JESUS>and have power to lay it down and to give it up,
        and I am authorized and have power to take it back. This command I have received
        from My Father.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'A division [of opinion] occurred again among the Jews because of
        these words [of His]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Many of them said, \u201CHe has a demon and He is mad [insane\u2014He
        raves and rambles]. Why listen to Him?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Jesus Asserts His Deity'
      title: Jesus Asserts His Deity
      number: 21
      content: "Others were saying, \u201CThese are not the words and thoughts of
        one possessed by a demon. Can a demon open the eyes of the blind?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'At that time the Feast of Dedication took place at Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "It was winter, and Jesus was walking in the temple [area] in Solomon\u2019s
        portico. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So the Jews surrounded Him and began saying to Him, \u201CHow long
        are You going to keep us in suspense? If You are [really] the Christ (the
        Messiah, the Anointed), tell us so plainly and openly.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jesus answered them, <JESUS>\u201CI have told you so, yet you do
        not believe. The works that I do in My Father\u2019s name testify concerning
        Me</JESUS> [they are My credentials and the evidence declaring who I am]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>But you do not believe Me</JESUS> [so you do not trust and
        follow Me] <JESUS>because you are not My sheep.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>The sheep that are My own hear My voice </JESUS>and listen
        to Me; I know them, and they follow Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '<JESUS>And I give them eternal life, and they will never, ever</JESUS>
        [by any means] <JESUS>perish; and no one will ever snatch them out of My
        hand.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>My Father, who has given </JESUS>them to Me, is greater and
        mightier than all; and no one is able to snatch them out of the Father\u2019s
        hand.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>I and the Father are One</JESUS> [in essence and nature].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Again the Jews picked up stones to stone Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Jesus answered them, <JESUS>\u201CI showed you many good works</JESUS>
        [and many acts of mercy] <JESUS>from the Father; for which of them are you
        stoning Me?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "The Jews answered Him, \u201CWe are not going to stone You for a
        good work, but for blasphemy, because You, a mere man, make Yourself out
        to be God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus answered them, <JESUS>\u201CIs it not written in your Law,
        \u2018I </JESUS>said, you are gods [human judges representing God, not divine
        beings]\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '<JESUS>If He </JESUS><JESUS>called them gods, men to whom the word
        of God came </JESUS>(and the Scripture cannot be undone or annulled or broken), '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "[if that is true] <JESUS>then do you say of Him whom the Father sanctified
        </JESUS>and set apart for Himself and sent into the world, \u2018You are
        blaspheming,\u2019 because I said, \u2018I am the Son of God\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: '<JESUS>If I do not do the works of My Father</JESUS> [that is, the
        miracles that only God could perform], <JESUS>then do not believe Me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>But if I am doing them, even if you do not believe Me </JESUS>or
        have faith in Me, [at least] <JESUS>believe the works</JESUS> [that I do\u2014admit
        that they are the works of God], <JESUS>so that you may know and keep on
        knowing</JESUS> [clearly\u2014without any doubt] <JESUS>that the Father is
        in Me, and I am in the Father</JESUS> [that is, I am One with Him].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'So they tried again to seize Him, but He eluded their grasp.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'He went back again across the Jordan to the place where John was
        first baptizing, and He was staying there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Many came to Him, and they were saying, \u201CJohn did not perform
        a single sign (attesting miracle), but everything John said about this Man
        was true and accurate.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: And many there believed and confidently trusted in Him [accepting
        Him as Savior, and following His teaching].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Death and Resurrection of Lazarus'
      title: The Death and Resurrection of Lazarus
      number: 1
      content: '  Now a certain man named Lazarus was sick. He was from Bethany,
        the village where Mary and her sister Martha lived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It was the Mary who anointed the Lord with perfume and wiped His
        feet with her hair, whose brother Lazarus was sick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So the sisters sent word to Him, saying, \u201CLord, he [our brother
        and Your friend] whom You love is sick.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When Jesus heard this, He said, <JESUS>\u201CThis sickness will not
        end in death; but</JESUS> [on the contrary it is] <JESUS>for the glory </JESUS>and
        honor of God, so that the Son of God may be glorified by it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now Jesus loved and was concerned about Martha and her sister and
        Lazarus [and considered them dear friends]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So [even] when He heard that Lazarus was sick, He stayed in the same
        place two more days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then He said to His disciples, <JESUS>\u201CLet us go back to Judea.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The disciples said to Him, \u201CRabbi (Teacher), the Jews were only
        recently going to stone You, and You are [thinking of] going back there again?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CAre there not twelve hours</JESUS> [of
        light] <JESUS>in the day? Anyone who walks in the daytime does not stumble,
        because he sees</JESUS> [by] <JESUS>the light of this world.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>But if anyone walks in the night, he stumbles, because there
        is no light in him.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He said this, and after that said, <JESUS>\u201COur friend Lazarus
        has fallen asleep; but I am going </JESUS>there to wake him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The disciples answered, \u201CLord, if he has fallen asleep, he will
        recover.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'However, Jesus had spoken of his death, but they thought that He
        was referring to natural sleep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So then Jesus told them plainly, <JESUS>\u201CLazarus is dead.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>And for your sake I am glad that I was not there, so that
        you may believe. But let us go to him.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Thomas, who was called Didymus (the twin), said to his fellow
        disciples, \u201CLet us go too, that we may die with Him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So when Jesus arrived, He found that Lazarus had already been in
        the tomb four days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Bethany was near Jerusalem, about two miles away; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and many of the Jews had come to see Martha and Mary, to comfort
        them concerning [the loss of] their brother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So when Martha heard that Jesus was coming, she went to meet Him,
        while Mary remained sitting in the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Martha said to Jesus, \u201CLord, if You had been here, my brother
        would not have died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Even now I know that whatever You ask of God, God will give to You.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus told her, <JESUS>\u201CYour brother will rise</JESUS> [from
        the dead].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Martha replied, \u201CI know that he will rise [from the dead] in
        the resurrection on the last day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jesus said to her, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>I am the Resurrection
        and the Life. Whoever believes in (adheres to, trusts in, relies on) Me</JESUS>
        [as Savior] <JESUS>will live even if he dies;</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>and everyone who lives and believes in Me</JESUS> [as Savior]
        <JESUS>will never die. Do you believe this?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "She said to Him, \u201CYes, Lord; I have believed and continue to
        believe that You are the Christ (the Messiah, the Anointed), the Son of God,
        He who was [destined and promised] to come into the world [and it is for
        You that the world has waited].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "After she had said this, she left and called her sister Mary, privately
        whispering [to her], \u201CThe Teacher is here and is asking for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And when she heard this, she got up quickly and went to Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now Jesus had not yet entered the village, but was still at the place
        where Martha had met Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'So when the Jews who were with her in the house comforting her, saw
        how quickly Mary got up and left, they followed her, assuming that she was
        going to the tomb to weep there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "When Mary came [to the place] where Jesus was and saw Him, she fell
        at His feet, saying to Him, \u201CLord, if You had been here, my brother
        would not have died.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When Jesus saw her sobbing, and the Jews who had come with her also
        sobbing, He was deeply moved in spirit [to the point of anger at the sorrow
        caused by death] and was troubled, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "and said, <JESUS>\u201CWhere have you laid him?\u201D</JESUS> They
        said, \u201CLord, come and see.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Jesus wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "So the Jews were saying, \u201CSee how He loved him [as a close friend]!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "But some of them said, \u201CCould not this Man, who opened the blind
        man\u2019s eyes, have kept this man from dying?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So Jesus, again deeply moved within [to the point of anger], approached
        the tomb. It was a cave, and a boulder was lying against it [to cover the
        entrance]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CTake away the stone.\u201D</JESUS> Martha,
        the sister of the dead man, said to Him, \u201CLord, by this time there will
        be an offensive odor, for he has been dead four days! [It is hopeless!]\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Jesus said to her, <JESUS>\u201CDid I not say to you that if you
        believe</JESUS> [in Me], <JESUS>you will see the glory of God</JESUS> [the
        expression of His excellence]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "So they took away the stone. And Jesus raised His eyes [toward heaven]
        and said, <JESUS>\u201CFather, I thank You that You have heard Me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "<JESUS>I knew that You always hear Me </JESUS>and listen to Me; but
        I have said this because of the people standing around, so that they may
        believe that You have sent Me [and that You have made Me Your representative].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "When He had said this, He shouted with a loud voice, <JESUS>\u201CLazarus,
        come out!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Out came the man who had been dead, his hands and feet tightly wrapped
        in burial cloths (linen strips), and with a [burial] cloth wrapped around
        his face. Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CUnwrap him and release him.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'So then, many of the Jews who had come to [be with] Mary and who
        were eyewitnesses to what Jesus had done, believed in Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: Conspiracy to Kill Jesus'
      title: Conspiracy to Kill Jesus
      number: 46
      content: 'But some of them went back to the Pharisees and told them what Jesus
        had done.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "So the chief priests and Pharisees convened a council [of the leaders
        in Israel], and said, \u201CWhat are we doing? For this man performs many
        signs (attesting miracles). "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "If we let Him go on like this, everyone will believe in Him, and
        the Romans will come and take away both our [holy] place (the temple) and
        our nation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "But one of them, Caiaphas, who was the high priest that year [the
        year of Christ\u2019s crucifixion], said to them, \u201CYou know nothing
        at all! "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Nor do you understand that it is expedient and politically advantageous
        for you that one man die for the people, and that the whole nation not perish.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Now he did not say this [simply] on his own initiative; but being
        the high priest that year, he [was unknowingly used by God and] prophesied
        that Jesus was going to die for the nation, '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'and not only for the nation, but also for the purpose of gathering
        together into one body the children of God who have been scattered abroad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'So from that day on they planned together to kill Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'For that reason Jesus no longer walked openly among the Jews, but
        left there and went to the district that borders on the uninhabited wilderness,
        to a town called Ephraim; and He stayed there with the disciples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'Now the Passover of the Jews was approaching, and many from the country
        went up to Jerusalem before Passover to purify themselves [ceremonially,
        so that they would be able to participate in the feast]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "So they were looking for Jesus as they stood in the temple [area],
        and saying among themselves, \u201CWhat do you think? Will He not come to
        the feast at all?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: Now the chief priests and Pharisees had given orders that if anyone
        knew where He was, he was to report it so that they might arrest Him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Mary Anoints Jesus'
      title: Mary Anoints Jesus
      number: 1
      content: '  Six days before the Passover, Jesus went to Bethany, where Lazarus
        was, whom He had raised from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So they gave a supper for Him there. Martha was serving, and Lazarus
        was one of those reclining at the table with Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Mary took a pound of very expensive perfume of pure nard, and
        she poured it on Jesus\u2019 feet and wiped His feet with her hair; and the
        house was filled with the fragrance of the perfume. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Judas Iscariot, one of His disciples, the one who was going to
        betray Him, said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CWhy was this perfume not sold for three hundred denarii and
        [the money] given to the poor?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now he said this, not because he cared about the poor [for he had
        never cared about them], but because he was a thief; and since he had the
        money box [serving as treasurer for the twelve disciples], he used to pilfer
        what was put into it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CLet her alone, so that she may keep</JESUS>
        [the rest of] <JESUS>it for the day of My burial.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>You always have the poor with you, but you do not always have
        Me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'A large crowd of Jews learned that He was there [at Bethany]; and
        they came, not only because of Jesus, but also to see Lazarus, whom He had
        raised from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the chief priests planned to kill Lazarus also, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Triumphal Entry'
      title: The Triumphal Entry
      number: 11
      content: 'because on account of him many of the Jews were going away [from
        the teaching and traditions of the Jewish leaders] and believing in Jesus
        [following Him as Savior and Messiah].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The next day, when the large crowd who had come to the Passover feast
        heard that Jesus was coming to Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "they took branches of palm trees [in homage to Him as King] and went
        out to meet Him, and they began shouting and kept shouting \u201CHosanna!
        Blessed (celebrated, praised) is He who comes in the name of the Lord, even
        the King of Israel!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Jesus, finding a young donkey, sat on it; just as it is written
        [in Scripture], '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CDo not fear, Daughter of Zion; Behold, Your King is coming,
        seated on a donkey\u2019s colt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'His disciples did not understand [the meaning of] these things at
        first; but when Jesus was glorified and exalted, they remembered that these
        things had been written about Him and had been done to Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So the people, who were with Him when He called Lazarus out of the
        tomb and raised him from the dead, continued to tell others about Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For this reason the crowd went to meet Him, because they heard that
        He had performed this [miraculous] sign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Greeks Seek Jesus'
      title: Greeks Seek Jesus
      number: 19
      content: "Then the Pharisees [argued and] said to one another, \u201CYou see
        that your efforts are futile. Look! The whole world has gone [running] after
        Him!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now there were some Greeks (Gentiles) among those who were going
        up to worship at the feast; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "these came to Philip, who was from Bethsaida in Galilee, with a request,
        saying, \u201CSir, we wish to see Jesus.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Philip came and told Andrew; then Andrew and Philip went and told
        Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Jesus answered them, <JESUS>\u201CThe hour has come for the Son
        of Man to be glorified </JESUS>and exalted.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '<JESUS>I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, unless
        a grain of wheat falls into the earth and dies, it remains alone [just one
        grain, never more]. <JESUS>But if it dies, it produces much grain </JESUS>and
        yields a harvest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '<JESUS>The one who loves his life</JESUS> [eventually] <JESUS>loses
        it</JESUS> [through death], <JESUS>but the one who hates his life in this
        world</JESUS> [and is concerned with pleasing God] <JESUS>will keep it for
        life eternal.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Jesus Foretells His Death'
      title: Jesus Foretells His Death
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>If anyone serves Me, he must</JESUS> [continue to faithfully]
        <JESUS>follow Me</JESUS> [without hesitation, holding steadfastly to Me,
        conforming to My example in living and, if need be, suffering or perhaps
        dying because of faith in Me]; <JESUS>and wherever I am</JESUS> [in heaven\u2019s
        glory], <JESUS>there will My servant be also. If anyone serves Me, the Father
        will honor him.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CNow My soul is troubled </JESUS>and deeply distressed;
        what shall I say? \u2018Father, save Me from this hour [of trial and agony]\u2019?
        <JESUS>But it is for this</JESUS> [very] <JESUS>purpose that I have come
        to this hour</JESUS> [this time and place]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "[Rather, I will say,] <JESUS>\u2018Father, glorify (honor, extol)
        Your name!\u2019\u2009\u201D</JESUS> Then a voice came from heaven saying,
        \u201CI have both glorified it, and will glorify it again.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "The crowd of people who stood nearby and heard the voice said that
        it had thundered; others said, \u201CAn angel has spoken to Him!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CThis voice has come for your sake, not
        for mine.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '<JESUS>Now judgment is upon this world</JESUS> [the sentence is being
        passed]. <JESUS>Now the ruler of this world (Satan) will be cast out.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>And I, if </JESUS>and when I am lifted up from the earth [on
        the cross], <JESUS>will draw all </JESUS>people to Myself [Gentiles, as well
        as Jews].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He said this to indicate the kind of death by which He was to die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "At this the crowd answered Him, \u201CWe have heard from the Law
        that the Christ is to remain forever; how then can You say, <JESUS>\u2018The
        Son of Man must be lifted up\u2019</JESUS>? Who is this Son of Man?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "So Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CThe Light is among you</JESUS>
        [only] <JESUS>a little while longer. Walk while you have the Light</JESUS>
        [keep on living by it], <JESUS>so that darkness will not overtake you. He
        who walks in the darkness does not know where he is going</JESUS> [he is
        drifting aimlessly]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>While you have the Light, believe </JESUS>and trust in the
        Light [have faith in it, hold on to it, rely on it], <JESUS>so that you may
        become sons of Light</JESUS> [being filled with Light as followers of God].\u201D 
        Jesus said these things, and then He left and hid Himself from them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Even though He had done so many signs (attesting miracles) right
        before them, yet they still did not believe and failed to trust Him\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "This was to fulfill what Isaiah the prophet said: \u201CLord, who
        has believed our message? And to whom has the arm (the power) of the Lord
        been shown (unveiled, revealed)?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Therefore they could not believe, for Isaiah said again, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CHe has blinded their eyes and He hardened their heart, to keep
        them from seeing with their eyes and understanding with their heart and being
        converted; otherwise, I [their God] would heal them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Isaiah said these things because he saw His glory and spoke about
        Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Nevertheless, even many of the leading men believed in Him [as Savior
        and Messiah], but because of the Pharisees they would not confess it, for
        fear that [if they acknowledged Him openly] they would be put out of the
        synagogue (excommunicated); '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'for they loved the approval of men more than the approval of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "But Jesus loudly declared, <JESUS>\u201CThe one who believes </JESUS>and
        trusts in Me does not believe [only] <JESUS>in Me but</JESUS> [also believes]
        <JESUS>in Him who sent Me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: '<JESUS>And whoever sees Me sees the One who sent Me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "<JESUS>I have come as Light into the world, so that everyone who
        believes </JESUS>and trusts in Me [as Savior\u2014all those who anchor their
        hope in Me and rely on the truth of My message] <JESUS>will not continue
        to live in darkness.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: '<JESUS>If anyone hears My words and does not keep them, I do not
        judge him; for I did not come to judge </JESUS>and condemn the world [that
        is, to initiate the final judgment of the world], <JESUS>but to save the
        world.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: '<JESUS>Whoever rejects Me and refuses to accept My teachings, has
        one who judges him; the </JESUS>very word that I spoke will judge and condemn
        him on the last day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: '<JESUS>For I have never spoken on My own initiative </JESUS>or authority,
        but the Father Himself who sent Me has given Me a commandment regarding what
        to say and what to speak.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "<JESUS>I know that His commandment is eternal life. So the things
        I speak, I speak</JESUS> [in accordance with His exact instruction,] <JESUS>just
        as the Father has told Me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Lord\u2019s Supper"
      title: "The Lord\u2019s Supper"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now before the Passover Feast, Jesus knew that His hour had come
        [and it was time] for Him to leave this world and return to the Father. Having
        [greatly] loved His own who were in the world, He loved them [and continuously
        loves them with His perfect love] to the end (eternally). '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "It was during supper, when the devil had already put [the thought
        of] betraying Jesus into the heart of Judas Iscariot, Simon\u2019s son, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'that Jesus, knowing that the Father had put everything into His hands,
        and that He had come from God and was [now] returning to God, '
      comments: []
    - name: "4: Jesus Washes the Disciples\u2019 Feet"
      title: "Jesus Washes the Disciples\u2019 Feet"
      number: 4
      content: "got up from supper, took off His [outer] robe, and taking a [servant\u2019s]
        towel, He tied it around His waist.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then He poured water into the basin and began washing the disciples\u2019
        feet and wiping them with the towel which was tied around His waist. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When He came to Simon Peter, he said to Him, \u201CLord, are You
        going to wash my feet?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Jesus replied to him, <JESUS>\u201CYou do not realize now what I
        am doing, but you will</JESUS> [fully] <JESUS>understand it later.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Peter said to Him, \u201CYou will never wash my feet!\u201D Jesus
        answered, <JESUS>\u201CUnless I wash you, you have no part with Me</JESUS>
        [we can have nothing to do with each other].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Simon Peter said to Him, \u201CLord, [in that case, wash] not only
        my feet, but also my hands and my head!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CAnyone who has bathed needs only
        to wash his feet, and is completely clean. And you</JESUS> [My disciples]
        <JESUS>are clean, but not all </JESUS>of you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For He knew who was going to betray Him; for that reason He said,
        <JESUS>\u201CNot all of you are clean.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So when He had washed their feet and put on His [outer] robe and
        reclined at the table again, He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CDo you understand
        what I have done for you?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '<JESUS>You call Me Teacher and Lord, and you are right in doing so,
        for </JESUS>that is who I am.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>So if I, the Lord and the Teacher, washed your feet, you ought
        to wash one another\u2019s feet as well.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>For I gave you</JESUS> [this as] <JESUS>an example, so that
        you should do</JESUS> [in turn] <JESUS>as I did to you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, a slave
        is not greater than his master, nor is one who is sent greater than the one
        who sent him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>If you know these things, you are blessed</JESUS> [happy and
        favored by God] <JESUS>if you put them into practice</JESUS> [and faithfully
        do them]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>I am not speaking of all of you. I know whom I have chosen;
        but</JESUS> [this has happened] <JESUS>in order that the Scripture may be
        fulfilled: \u2018H</JESUS>e who eats My bread has raised up his heel against
        Me  [as My enemy].\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>From now on I am telling you</JESUS> [what will happen] <JESUS>before
        it occurs, so that when it does take place you may believe that I am </JESUS>He
        [who I say I am\u2014the Christ, the Anointed, the Messiah]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Jesus Predicts His Betrayal'
      title: Jesus Predicts His Betrayal
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, the one
        who receives and welcomes whomever I send receives Me; and the one who receives
        Me receives Him who sent Me [in that same way].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "After Jesus had said these things, He was troubled in spirit, and
        testified and said, <JESUS>\u201CI assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say
        to you, one of you will betray Me and hand Me over.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The disciples began looking at one another, puzzled and disturbed
        as to whom He could mean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "One of His disciples, whom Jesus loved (esteemed), was leaning against
        Jesus\u2019 chest. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So Simon Peter motioned to him (John) and [quietly] asked [him to
        ask Jesus] of whom He was speaking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then leaning back against Jesus\u2019 chest, he (John) asked Him
        [privately], \u201CLord, who is it?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CIt is the one to whom I am going to
        give this piece</JESUS> [of bread] <JESUS>after I have dipped it.\u201D</JESUS>
        So when He had dipped the piece of bread [into the dish], He gave it to Judas,
        son of Simon Iscariot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "After [Judas had taken] the piece of bread, Satan entered him. Then
        Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CWhat you are going to do, do quickly</JESUS>
        [without delay].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But no one reclining at the table knew why He said this to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Some thought that, since Judas [as the treasurer of the group] had
        the money box, Jesus was telling him, \u201CBuy what we need for the feast,\u201D
        or that he was to give something to the poor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'After taking the piece of bread, he went out immediately; and it
        was night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So when Judas had left, Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CNow is</JESUS> [the
        time for] <JESUS>the Son of Man</JESUS> [to be] <JESUS>glorified, and God
        is glorified in Him;</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '<JESUS>[</JESUS>if God is glorified in Him,] God will also glorify
        Him (the Son) in Himself, and will glorify Him at once.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>Little children, I am with you</JESUS> [only] <JESUS>a little
        longer. You will look for Me and, as I told the Jews, so I tell you now,
        \u2018Where I am going, you are not able to come.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '<JESUS>I am giving you a new commandment, that you </JESUS><JESUS>love
        one another. Just as I have loved you, so you too are to love one another.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>By this everyone will know that you are My disciples, if you
        have love </JESUS>and unselfish concern for one another.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Simon Peter said to Him, \u201CLord, where are You going?\u201D Jesus
        answered, <JESUS>\u201CWhere I am going, you cannot follow Me now; but you
        will be able to follow later.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Peter said to Him, \u201CLord, why cannot I follow You now? I will
        lay down my life for You!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CWill you</JESUS> [really] <JESUS>lay
        down your life for Me? I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you,
        before a rooster crows you will deny and completely disown Me three times."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Comforts His Disciples'
      title: Jesus Comforts His Disciples
      number: 1
      content: "    <JESUS>\u201CDo not let your heart be troubled (afraid, cowardly).
        Believe</JESUS> [confidently] <JESUS>in God </JESUS>and trust in Him, [have
        faith, hold on to it, rely on it, keep going and] <JESUS>believe also in
        Me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<JESUS>In My Father\u2019s house are many dwelling places. If it
        were not so, I would have told you, because I am going there to prepare a
        place for you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>And if I go and prepare a place for you, I will come back
        again and I will take you to Myself, so that where I am you may be also.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>And</JESUS> [to the place] <JESUS>where I am going, you know
        the way.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Thomas said to Him, \u201CLord, we do not know where You are going;
        so how can we know the way?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "6: Jesus\u2019 Oneness with the Father"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Oneness with the Father"
      number: 6
      content: "Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>I am the</JESUS> [only]
        <JESUS>Way</JESUS> [to God] <JESUS>and the</JESUS> [real] <JESUS>Truth and
        the</JESUS> [real] <JESUS>Life; no one comes to the Father but through Me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  <JESUS>If you had</JESUS> [really] <JESUS>known Me, you would also
        have known My Father. From now on you know Him, and have seen Him.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Philip said to Him, \u201CLord, show us the Father and then we will
        be satisfied.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CHave I been with you for so long
        a time, and you do not know Me yet, Philip, </JESUS>nor recognize clearly
        who I am? Anyone who has seen Me has seen the Father. How can you say, \u2018Show
        us the Father?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<JESUS>Do you not believe that I am in the Father, and the Father
        is in Me? The words I say to you I do not say on My own initiative </JESUS>or
        authority, but the Father, abiding continually in Me, does His works [His
        attesting miracles and acts of power]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>Believe Me that I am in the Father and the Father is in Me;
        otherwise believe</JESUS> [Me] <JESUS>because of the</JESUS> [very] <JESUS>works
        themselves</JESUS> [which you have witnessed]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, anyone
        who believes in Me [as Savior] <JESUS>will also do the things that I do;
        and he will do even greater things than these</JESUS> [in extent and outreach],
        <JESUS>because I am going to the Father.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '<JESUS>And I will do whatever you ask in My name</JESUS> [as My representative],
        <JESUS>this I will do, so that the Father may be glorified </JESUS>and celebrated
        in the Son.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>If you ask Me anything in My name</JESUS> [as My representative],
        <JESUS>I will do it.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Role of the Spirit'
      title: Role of the Spirit
      number: 15
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CIf you</JESUS> [really] <JESUS>love Me, you will keep
        </JESUS>and obey My commandments.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>And I will ask the Father, and He will give you another
        </JESUS>    <JESUS>Helper (Comforter, Advocate, Intercessor\u2014Counselor,
        Strengthener, Standby), to be with you forever\u2014</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>the Spirit of Truth, whom the world cannot receive</JESUS>
        [and take to its heart] <JESUS>because it does not see Him or know Him, </JESUS>but
        you know Him because He (the Holy Spirit) remains with you continually and
        will be in you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI will not leave you as orphans</JESUS> [comfortless,
        bereaved, and helpless]; <JESUS>I will come</JESUS> [back] <JESUS>to you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>After a little while the world will no longer see Me, but
        you will see Me; because I live, you will live also.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<JESUS>On that day</JESUS> [when that time comes] <JESUS>you will
        know for yourselves that I am in My Father, and you </JESUS>are in Me, and
        I am in you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>The person who has My commandments and keeps them is the one
        who</JESUS> [really] <JESUS>loves Me; and whoever</JESUS> [really] <JESUS>loves
        Me will be loved by My Father, and I will love him and reveal Myself to him</JESUS>
        [I will make Myself real to him].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Judas (not Iscariot) asked Him, \u201CLord, what has happened that
        You are going to reveal Yourself to us and not to the world?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CIf anyone</JESUS> [really] <JESUS>loves
        Me, he will keep My word (teaching); and My Father will love him, and We
        will come to him and make Our dwelling place with him.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>One who does not</JESUS> [really] <JESUS>love Me does not
        keep My words. And the word (teaching) which you hear is not Mine, but is
        the Father\u2019s who sent Me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI have told you these things while I am still with
        you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>But the </JESUS><JESUS>Helper (Comforter, Advocate, Intercessor\u2014Counselor,
        Strengthener, Standby), the Holy Spirit, whom the Father will send in My
        name</JESUS> [in My place, to represent Me and act on My behalf], <JESUS>He
        will teach you all things. And He will help you remember everything that
        I have told you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>Peace I leave with you; My</JESUS> [perfect] <JESUS>peace
        I give to you; not as the world gives do I give to you. Do not let your heart
        be troubled, nor let it be afraid.</JESUS> [Let My perfect peace calm you
        in every circumstance and give you courage and strength for every challenge.] '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>You heard Me tell you, \u2018I am going away, and I am coming
        </JESUS>back to you.\u2019 If you [really] <JESUS>loved Me, you would have
        rejoiced, because I am going</JESUS> [back] <JESUS>to the Father, for </JESUS><JESUS>the
        Father is greater than I.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '<JESUS>I have told you now before it happens, so that when it does
        take place, you may believe </JESUS>and have faith [in Me]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '<JESUS>I will not speak with you much longer, for the ruler of the
        world (Satan) is coming. And he has no claim on Me</JESUS> [no power over
        Me nor anything that he can use against Me]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: <JESUS>but so that the world may know</JESUS> [without any doubt]
        <JESUS>that I love the Father, I do exactly as the Father has commanded Me</JESUS>
        [and act in full agreement with Him]. <JESUS>Get up, let us go from here.</JESUS>
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jesus Is the Vine\u2014Followers Are Branches"
      title: "Jesus Is the Vine\u2014Followers Are Branches"
      number: 1
      content: "    <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS>    <JESUS>I am the true Vine, and My Father
        is the vinedresser.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '<JESUS>Every branch in Me that does not bear fruit, He takes away;
        and every </JESUS>branch that continues to bear fruit, He [repeatedly] <JESUS>prunes,
        so that it will bear more fruit</JESUS> [even richer and finer fruit]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>You are already clean because of the word which I have given
        you</JESUS> [the teachings which I have discussed with you]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>Remain in Me, and I</JESUS> [will remain] <JESUS>in you. Just
        as no branch can bear fruit by itself without remaining in the vine, neither
        can you</JESUS> [bear fruit, producing evidence of your faith] <JESUS>unless
        you remain in Me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '<JESUS>I am the Vine; you are the branches. The one who remains in
        Me and I in him bears much fruit, for</JESUS> [otherwise] <JESUS>apart from
        Me</JESUS> [that is, cut off from vital union with Me] <JESUS>you can do
        nothing.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<JESUS>If anyone does not remain in Me, he is thrown out like a</JESUS>
        [broken off] <JESUS>branch, and withers </JESUS>and dies; and they gather
        such branches and throw them into the fire, and they are burned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '<JESUS>If you remain in Me and My words remain in you</JESUS> [that
        is, if we are vitally united and My message lives in your heart], <JESUS>ask
        whatever you wish and it will be done for you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>My Father is glorified </JESUS>and honored by this, when you
        bear much fruit, and prove yourselves to be My [true] <JESUS>disciples.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '<JESUS>I have loved you just as the Father has loved Me; remain in
        My love</JESUS> [and do not doubt My love for you]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>If you keep My commandments </JESUS>and obey My teaching,
        you will remain in My love, just as I have kept My Father\u2019s commandments
        and remain in His love.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "11: Disciples\u2019 Relation to Each Other"
      title: "Disciples\u2019 Relation to Each Other"
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>I have told you these things so that My joy </JESUS>and delight
        may be in you, and that your joy may be made full and complete and overflowing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CThis is My commandment, that you </JESUS>    <JESUS>love
        </JESUS>and unselfishly seek the best for one another, just as I have loved
        you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '<JESUS>No one has greater love</JESUS> [nor stronger commitment]
        <JESUS>than to lay down his own life for his friends.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>You are my friends if you keep on doing what I command you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>I do not call you servants any longer, for the servant does
        not know what his master is doing; but I have called you</JESUS> [My] <JESUS>friends,
        because I have revealed to you everything that I have heard from My Father.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>You have not chosen Me, but I have chosen you and I have appointed
        </JESUS>and placed and purposefully planted you, so that you would go and
        bear fruit and keep on bearing, and that your fruit will remain and be lasting,
        so that whatever you ask of the Father in My name [as My representative]
        <JESUS>He may give to you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: "17: Disciples\u2019 Relation to the World"
      title: "Disciples\u2019 Relation to the World"
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>This</JESUS> [is what] <JESUS>I command you: that you love
        </JESUS>and unselfishly seek the best for one another.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CIf the world hates you</JESUS> [and it does], <JESUS>know
        that it has hated Me before </JESUS>it hated you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>If you belonged to the world, the world would love</JESUS>
        [you as] <JESUS>its own </JESUS>and would treat you with affection. But you
        are not of the world [you no longer belong to it], <JESUS>but I have chosen
        you out of the world. And because of this the world hates you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>Remember</JESUS> [and continue to remember] <JESUS>that I
        told you, \u2018A servant is not greater than his master.\u2019 If they persecuted
        Me, they will also persecute you. If they kept My word, they will keep yours
        also.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>But they will do all these</JESUS> [hurtful] <JESUS>things
        to you for My name\u2019s sake</JESUS> [because you bear My name and are
        identified with Me], <JESUS>for they do not know the One who sent Me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '<JESUS>If I had not come and spoken to them, they would not have</JESUS>
        [the guilt of their] <JESUS>sin; but now they have no excuse for their sin.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '<JESUS>The one who hates Me also hates My Father.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '<JESUS>If I had not done among them the works (attesting miracles)
        which no one else</JESUS> [ever] <JESUS>did, they would not have</JESUS>
        [the guilt of their] <JESUS>sin; but now</JESUS> [the fact is that] <JESUS>they
        have both seen</JESUS> [these works] <JESUS>and have hated Me</JESUS> [and
        continue to hate Me] <JESUS>and My Father as well.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>But</JESUS> [this is so] <JESUS>that the word which has been
        written in their Law would be fulfilled, \u2018T</JESUS>hey hated Me without
        a cause.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut when the </JESUS>    <JESUS>Helper (Comforter,
        Advocate, Intercessor\u2014Counselor, Strengthener, Standby) comes, whom
        I will send to you from the Father, </JESUS>that is the Spirit of Truth who
        comes from the Father, He will testify and bear witness about Me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: <JESUS>But you will testify also </JESUS>and be My witnesses, because
        you have been with Me from the beginning.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jesus\u2019 Warning"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Warning"
      number: 1
      content: "    <JESUS>\u201CI have told you these things so that you will not
        stumble </JESUS>or be caught off guard and fall away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '<JESUS>They will put you out of the synagogues </JESUS>and make you
        outcasts. And a time is coming when whoever kills you will think that he
        is offering service to God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>And they will do these things because they have not known
        the Father or Me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Holy Spirit Promised'
      title: The Holy Spirit Promised
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>I have told you these things</JESUS> [now], <JESUS>so that
        when their time comes, you will remember that I told you about them. I did
        not say these things to you at the beginning, because I was with you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CBut now I am going to Him who sent Me; and none of
        you asks Me, \u2018Where are You going?\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<JESUS>But because I have said these things to you, sorrow has filled
        your hearts</JESUS> [and taken complete possession of them]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>But I tell you the truth, it is to your advantage that I go
        away; for if I do not go away, the </JESUS><JESUS>Helper (Comforter, Advocate,
        Intercessor\u2014Counselor, Strengthener, Standby) will not come to you;
        but if I go, I will send Him (the Holy Spirit) to you</JESUS> [to be in close
        fellowship with you]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>And He, when He comes, will convict the world about</JESUS>
        [the guilt of] <JESUS>sin</JESUS> [and the need for a Savior], <JESUS>and
        about righteousness, and about judgment:</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '<JESUS>about sin</JESUS> [and the true nature of it], <JESUS>because
        they do not believe in Me</JESUS> [and My message]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<JESUS>about righteousness</JESUS> [personal integrity and godly
        character], <JESUS>because I am going to My Father and you will no longer
        see Me;</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>about judgment</JESUS> [the certainty of it], <JESUS>because
        the ruler of this world (Satan) has been judged </JESUS>and condemned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI have many more things to say to you, but you cannot
        bear</JESUS> [to hear] <JESUS>them now.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>But when He, the Spirit of Truth, comes, He will guide you
        into all the truth</JESUS> [full and complete truth]. <JESUS>For He will
        not speak on His own initiative, but He will speak whatever He hears</JESUS>
        [from the Father\u2014the message regarding the Son], <JESUS>and He will
        disclose to you what is to come</JESUS> [in the future]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>He will glorify </JESUS>and honor Me, because He (the Holy
        Spirit) will take from what is Mine and will disclose it to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "15: Jesus\u2019 Death and Resurrection Foretold"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Death and Resurrection Foretold"
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>All things that the Father has are Mine. Because of this I
        said that He</JESUS> [the Spirit] <JESUS>will take from what is Mine and
        will reveal it to you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CA little while, and you will no longer see Me; and
        again a little while, and you will see Me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Some of His disciples said to one another, \u201CWhat does He mean
        when He tells us, <JESUS>\u2018A little while, and you will not see Me; and
        again a little while, and you will see Me\u2019</JESUS>; and, <JESUS>\u2018because
        I am going to My Father\u2019?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So they were saying, \u201CWhat does He mean when He says, <JESUS>\u2018A
        little while\u2019</JESUS>? We do not know what He is talking about.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Jesus knew that they wanted to ask Him, so He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CAre
        you wondering among yourselves about what I meant when I said, \u2018A little
        while, and you will not see Me, and again a little while, and you will see
        Me\u2019?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<JESUS>I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, that you
        will weep and grieve [in great mourning], <JESUS>but the world will rejoice.
        You will be sorrowful, but your sorrow will be turned into joy.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '<JESUS>A woman, when she is in labor, has pain because her time</JESUS>
        [to give birth] <JESUS>has come; but when she has given birth to the child,
        she no longer remembers the anguish because of her joy that a child has come
        into the world.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Prayer Promises'
      title: Prayer Promises
      number: 22
      content: '<JESUS>So for now you are in grief; but I will see you again, and</JESUS>
        [then] <JESUS>your hearts will rejoice, and no one will take away from you
        your</JESUS> [great] <JESUS>joy.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  <JESUS>In that day you will not</JESUS> [need to] <JESUS>ask Me
        about anything. I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, whatever
        you ask the Father in My name [as My representative], <JESUS>He will give
        you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '<JESUS>Until now you have not asked</JESUS> [the Father] <JESUS>for
        anything in My name; but now ask </JESUS>and keep on asking and you will
        receive, so that your joy may be full and complete.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI have told you these things in figurative language
        (veiled language, proverbs); the hour is now coming when I will no longer
        speak to you in figures of speech, but I will tell you plainly about the
        Father.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>In that day you will ask in My name, and I am not saying to
        you that I will ask the Father on your behalf</JESUS> [because it will be
        unnecessary]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>for the Father Himself</JESUS> [tenderly] <JESUS>loves you,
        because you have loved Me and have believed that I came from the Father.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>I came from the Father and have come into the world; again,
        I am leaving the world and going to the Father.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "His disciples said, \u201CAh, now You are speaking plainly to us
        and not in figures of speech! "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Now we know that You know all things, and have no need for anyone
        to question You; because of this we believe [without any doubt] that you
        came from God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Jesus answered them, <JESUS>\u201CDo you now</JESUS> [at last] <JESUS>believe?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '<JESUS>Take careful notice: an hour is coming, and has arrived, when
        you will all be scattered, each to his own </JESUS>home, leaving Me alone;
        and yet I am not alone, because the Father is with Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>I have told you these things, so that in Me you may have</JESUS>
        [perfect] <JESUS>peace. In the world you have tribulation </JESUS>and distress
        and suffering, but be courageous [be confident, be undaunted, be filled with
        joy]; <JESUS>I have overcome the world.\u201D</JESUS> [My conquest is accomplished,
        My victory abiding.]"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The High Priestly Prayer'
      title: The High Priestly Prayer
      number: 1
      content: "  When Jesus had spoken these things, He raised His eyes to heaven
        [in prayer] and said, <JESUS>\u201CFather, the </JESUS><JESUS>hour has come.
        Glorify Your Son, so that Your Son may glorify You.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<JESUS>Just as You have given Him power </JESUS>and authority over
        all mankind, [now glorify Him] <JESUS>so that He may give eternal life </JESUS><JESUS>to
        all whom You have given Him</JESUS> [to be His\u2014permanently and forever]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>Now this is eternal life: that they may know You, the only
        true</JESUS> [supreme and sovereign] <JESUS>God, and</JESUS> [in the same
        manner know] <JESUS>Jesus</JESUS> [as the] <JESUS>Christ whom You have sent.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>I have glorified You</JESUS> [down here] <JESUS>on the earth
        by </JESUS><JESUS>completing the work that You gave Me to do.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '<JESUS>Now, Father, glorify Me together with Yourself, with the glory
        </JESUS>and majesty that I had with You before the world existed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI have manifested Your name</JESUS> [and revealed
        Your very self, Your real self] <JESUS>to the people whom You have given
        Me out of the world; they were Yours and You gave them to Me, and they have
        kept </JESUS>and obeyed Your word.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '<JESUS>Now</JESUS> [at last] <JESUS>they know</JESUS> [with confident
        assurance] <JESUS>that all You have given Me is from You</JESUS> [it is really
        and truly Yours]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>For the words which You gave Me I have given them; and they
        received </JESUS>and accepted them and truly understood [with confident assurance]
        <JESUS>that I came from You</JESUS> [from Your presence], <JESUS>and they
        believed</JESUS> [without any doubt] <JESUS>that You sent Me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '<JESUS>I pray for them; I do not pray for the world, but for those
        You have given Me, because they belong to You;</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '<JESUS>and all things that are Mine are Yours, and</JESUS> [all things
        that are] <JESUS>Yours are Mine; and I am glorified in them.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>I am no longer in the world; yet they are still in the world,
        and I am coming to You. Holy Father, keep them in Your name, </JESUS>the
        name which You have given Me, so that they may be one just as We are.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Disciples in the World'
      title: The Disciples in the World
      number: 12
      content: '<JESUS>While I was with them, I was keeping them in Your name which
        You have given Me; and I guarded them </JESUS>and protected them, and not
        one of them was lost except <JESUS>the son of destruction, so that the Scripture
        would be fulfilled.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  <JESUS>But now I am coming to You; and I say these things</JESUS>
        [while I am still] <JESUS>in the world so that they may experience My joy
        made full </JESUS>and complete and perfect within them [filling their hearts
        with My delight]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>I have given to them Your word</JESUS> [the message You gave
        Me]; <JESUS>and the world has hated them because they are not of the world
        </JESUS>and do not belong to the world, just as I am not of the world and
        do not belong to it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '<JESUS>I do not ask You to take them out of the world, but that You
        keep them </JESUS>and protect them from the evil one.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>They are not of the world, just as I am not of the world.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>Sanctify them in the truth</JESUS> [set them apart for Your
        purposes, make them holy]; <JESUS>Your word is truth.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '<JESUS>Just as You commissioned </JESUS>and sent Me into the world,
        I also have commissioned and sent them (believers) into the world.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>For their sake </JESUS><JESUS>I sanctify Myself</JESUS> [to
        do Your will], <JESUS>so that they also may be sanctified</JESUS> [set apart,
        dedicated, made holy] <JESUS>in</JESUS> [Your] <JESUS>truth.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CI do not pray for these alone</JESUS> [it is not for
        their sake only that I make this request], <JESUS>but also for</JESUS> [all]
        <JESUS>those who</JESUS> [will ever] <JESUS>believe </JESUS>and trust in
        Me through their message,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Their Future Glory'
      title: Their Future Glory
      number: 21
      content: '<JESUS>that they all may be one; just as You, Father, are in Me and
        I in You, that they also may be one in Us, so that the world may believe</JESUS>
        [without any doubt] <JESUS>that You sent Me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  <JESUS>I have given to them the glory </JESUS>and honor which You
        have given Me, that they may be one, just as We are one;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '<JESUS>I in them and You in Me, that they may be perfected </JESUS>and
        completed into one, so that the world may know [without any doubt] <JESUS>that
        You sent Me, and</JESUS> [that You] <JESUS>have loved them, just as You have
        loved Me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '<JESUS>Father, I desire that they also, whom You have given to Me</JESUS>
        [as Your gift to Me], <JESUS>may be with Me where I am, so that they may
        see My glory which You have given Me, because You loved Me before the foundation
        of the world.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  <JESUS>\u201CO just </JESUS>and righteous Father, although the
        world has not known You and has never acknowledged You [and the revelation
        of Your mercy], <JESUS>yet I have </JESUS>always known You; and these [believers]
        <JESUS>know</JESUS> [without any doubt] <JESUS>that You sent Me;</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>and I have made Your name known to them, and will </JESUS>continue
        to make it known, so that the love with which You have loved Me may be in
        them [overwhelming their heart], <JESUS>and I</JESUS> [may be] <JESUS>in
        them.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judas Betrays Jesus'
      title: Judas Betrays Jesus
      number: 1
      content: '  Having said these things, Jesus left with His disciples and went
        across the ravine of the Kidron. There was a garden there, which He and His
        disciples entered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now Judas, who was betraying Him, knew the place, because Jesus had
        often met there with His disciples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Judas, having obtained the Roman  cohort and some officers from
        the high priests and the Pharisees, came there with lanterns and torches
        and weapons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Jesus, knowing all that was about to happen to Him, went to
        them and asked, <JESUS>\u201CWhom do you want?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They answered Him, \u201CJesus the Nazarene.\u201D Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CI
        am </JESUS>He.\u201D And Judas, who was betraying Him, was also standing
        with them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CI am </JESUS>He,\u201D they drew back
        and fell to the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Again He asked them, <JESUS>\u201CWhom do you want?\u201D</JESUS>
        And they said, \u201CJesus the Nazarene.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CI told you that I am </JESUS>He; so
        if you want Me, let these men go on their way.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "This was to fulfill and verify the words He had spoken, <JESUS>\u201COf
        those whom You have given Me, I have not lost even one.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Simon Peter, who had a sword, drew it and struck the high priest\u2019s
        servant, cutting off his right ear. The servant\u2019s name was Malchus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Jesus before Annas and Caiaphas'
      title: Jesus before Annas and Caiaphas
      number: 11
      content: "So Jesus said to Peter, <JESUS>\u201CPut the sword</JESUS> [back]
        <JESUS>in its sheath! Shall I not drink the cup which My Father has given
        Me?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So the cohort and their commander and the officers of the Jews arrested
        Jesus and bound Him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and led Him to Annas first; for he was the father-in-law of Caiaphas,
        who was high priest that year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'It was Caiaphas who had advised the Jews that it was expedient for
        one man to die on behalf of the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Simon Peter and another disciple were following Jesus. Now that disciple
        was known to the high priest, so he went with Jesus into the courtyard of
        the [residence of the] high priest; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'but Peter was standing outside at the door. So the other disciple
        (John), who was known to the high priest, went out and spoke to the doorkeeper,
        and brought Peter inside. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then the servant girl who kept the door said to Peter, \u201CYou
        are not one of this Man\u2019s disciples, are you?\u201D He said, \u201CI
        am not.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the servants and the officers had made a fire of coals, because
        it was cold, and they were standing and warming themselves. And Peter was
        with them, standing and warming himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then the high priest questioned Jesus about His disciples and about
        His teaching. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Jesus answered him, <JESUS>\u201CI have spoken openly to the world.
        I always taught in a synagogue and in the temple</JESUS> [area], <JESUS>where
        all the Jews </JESUS>habitually congregate; and I said nothing in secret.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>Why question Me? Question those who have heard what I said
        to them. They know what I said.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But when He said this, one of the officers who was standing nearby
        struck Jesus [in the face], saying, \u201CIs that how You answer the high
        priest?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CIf I have said </JESUS>anything wrong,
        make a formal statement about the wrong; but if [I spoke] <JESUS>properly,
        why did you strike Me?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: "24: Peter\u2019s Denial of Jesus"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Denial of Jesus"
      number: 24
      content: 'So Annas sent Him bound to Caiaphas the high priest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now Simon Peter was [still] standing and warming himself. So they
        said to him, \u201CYou are not one of His disciples, are you?\u201D He denied
        it and said, \u201CI am not.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "One of the high priest\u2019s servants, a relative of the one whose
        ear Peter cut off, said, \u201CDid I not see you with Him in the garden?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Jesus before Pilate'
      title: Jesus before Pilate
      number: 27
      content: 'So Peter denied it again, and immediately a rooster crowed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then the Jews led Jesus from Caiaphas to the Praetorium (governor\u2019s
        palace). Now it was early and the Jews did not enter the Praetorium so that
        they would not be [ceremonially] unclean, but might [be able to] eat [and
        participate in the Feast of Unleavened Bread which began after] the Passover
        [supper]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So Pilate came out to them and asked, \u201CWhat accusation do you
        bring against this Man?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "They answered, \u201CIf He were not a criminal, we would not have
        handed Him over to you [for judgment].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Pilate said to them, \u201CTake Him yourselves and judge Him
        according to your own law.\u201D The Jews said, \u201CWe are not permitted
        to put anyone to death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'This was to fulfill the word which Jesus had spoken to indicate by
        what manner of death He was going to die.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So Pilate went into the Praetorium again, and called Jesus and asked
        Him, \u201CAre You the King of the Jews?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CAre you saying this on your own initiative,
        or did others tell you about Me?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Pilate answered, \u201CI am not a Jew, am I? Your own people and
        their chief priests have handed You over to me. What have You done [that
        is worthy of death]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CMy kingdom is not of this world</JESUS>
        [nor does it have its origin in this world]. <JESUS>If My kingdom were of
        this world, My servants would be fighting</JESUS> [hard] <JESUS>to keep Me
        from being handed over to the Jews; but as it is, My kingdom is not of this
        world.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "So Pilate said to Him, \u201CThen You are a King?\u201D Jesus answered,
        <JESUS>\u201CYou say</JESUS> [correctly] <JESUS>that I am a King. This is
        why I was born, and for this I have come into the world, to testify to the
        truth. Everyone who is of the truth</JESUS> [who is a friend of the truth
        and belongs to the truth] <JESUS>hears </JESUS>and listens carefully to My
        voice.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Pilate said to Him [scornfully], \u201CWhat is truth?\u201D  And
        when he had said this, he went out to the Jews again and told them, \u201CI
        find no guilt in Him [no crime, no cause for an accusation]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "But you have a custom that I release someone for you at the Passover.
        So shall I release for you the King of the Jews?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then they all shouted back again, \u201CNot this Man, but Barabbas!\u201D
        Now Barabbas was a robber."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Crown of Thorns'
      title: The Crown of Thorns
      number: 1
      content: '  So then Pilate took Jesus and had Him scourged (flogged, whipped). '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the soldiers twisted together a crown of thorns and put it on
        His head, and put a purple robe around Him; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and they kept coming up to Him, saying [mockingly], \u201CHail, King
        of the Jews [Good health! Peace! Long life to you, King of the Jews]!\u201D
        And they slapped Him in the face. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Pilate came out again and said to them, \u201CLook, I am bringing
        Him out to you so that you may know that I find no guilt in Him [no crime,
        no cause for an accusation].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So Jesus came out, wearing the crown of thorns and the purple robe,
        and Pilate said to them, \u201CLook! The Man!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When the chief priests and officers saw Him, they shouted, \u201CCrucify
        [Him]! Crucify [Him]!\u201D Pilate said to them, \u201CTake Him yourselves
        and crucify Him, for I find no guilt in Him [no crime, no cause for an accusation].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Jews answered him, \u201CWe have a law [regarding blasphemy],
        and according to that law He should die, because He made Himself out to be
        the Son of God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So when Pilate heard this said, he was [even] more alarmed and afraid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He went into the Praetorium again and said to Jesus, \u201CWhere
        are You from?\u201D But Jesus did not answer him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So Pilate said to Him, \u201CYou do not speak to me? Do You not know
        that I have authority to release You, and I have authority to crucify You?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CYou would have no authority over Me
        at all if it had not been given to you from above. For this reason the sin
        </JESUS>and guilt of the <JESUS>one who handed Me over to you is greater</JESUS>
        [than your own].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "As a result of this, Pilate kept making efforts to release Him, but
        the Jews kept screaming, \u201CIf you release this Man, you are no friend
        of Caesar! Anyone who makes himself out [to be] a king opposes Caesar [and
        rebels against the emperor]!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When Pilate heard this, he brought Jesus out, and sat down on the
        judgment seat at a place called The Pavement, but in Hebrew, Gabbatha. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now it was the day of Preparation for the Passover [week], and it
        was about the sixth hour (noon). He said to the Jews, \u201CLook, your King!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Crucifixion'
      title: The Crucifixion
      number: 15
      content: "But they shouted, \u201CAway with Him, away with Him, crucify Him!\u201D
        Pilate said to them, \u201CShall I crucify your King?\u201D The chief priests
        answered, \u201CWe have no king but Caesar!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then he handed Him over to them to be crucified.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So they took Jesus, and He went out, bearing His own cross, to the
        place called the Place of the Skull, which is called in Hebrew, Golgotha. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'There they crucified Him, and with Him two others, one on either
        side, and Jesus between them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Pilate also wrote an inscription [on a placard] and put it on the
        cross. And it was written: \u201CJESUS THE NAZARENE, THE KING OF THE JEWS.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And many of the Jews read this inscription, for the place where Jesus
        was crucified was near the city; and it was written in Hebrew, in Latin,
        and in Greek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then the chief priests of the Jews said to Pilate, \u201CDo not write,
        \u2018The King of the Jews\u2019; but, \u2018He said, \u201CI am King of
        the Jews.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Pilate replied, \u201CWhat I have written I have written [and it
        remains written].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then the soldiers, when they had crucified Jesus, took His outer
        clothes and made four parts, a part for each soldier, and also the tunic.
        But the tunic was seamless, woven [in one piece] from the top throughout. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So they said to one another, \u201CLet us not tear it, but cast lots
        for it, to decide whose it will be.\u201D This was to fulfill the Scripture,
        \u201CThey divided My outer clothing among them, and for My clothing they
        cast lots.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So the soldiers did these things.  But standing by the cross of Jesus
        were His mother, His mother\u2019s sister [Salome], Mary the wife of Clopas,
        and Mary Magdalene. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So Jesus, seeing His mother, and the disciple whom He loved (esteemed)
        standing near, said to His mother, \u201C[Dear] <JESUS>woman, look,</JESUS>
        [here is] <JESUS>your son!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then He said to the disciple (John), <JESUS>\u201CLook!</JESUS> [here
        is] <JESUS>your mother</JESUS> [protect and provide for her]!\u201D From
        that hour the disciple took her into his own home.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "After this, Jesus, knowing that all was now finished, said in fulfillment
        of the Scripture, <JESUS>\u201CI am thirsty.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'A jar full of sour wine was placed there; so they put a sponge soaked
        in the sour wine on [a branch of] hyssop and held it to His mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Care of the Body of Jesus'
      title: Care of the Body of Jesus
      number: 30
      content: "When Jesus had received the sour wine, He said, <JESUS>\u201CIt is
        finished!\u201D</JESUS> And He bowed His head and [voluntarily] gave up His
        spirit.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Since it was the day of Preparation [for the Sabbath], in order to
        prevent the bodies from hanging on the cross on the Sabbath (for that Sabbath
        was a high holy day) the Jews asked Pilate to have their legs broken [to
        hasten death] and the bodies taken away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So the soldiers came and broke the legs of the first man, and of
        the other who had been crucified with Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'But when they came to Jesus and saw that He was already dead, they
        did not break His legs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But one of the soldiers pierced His side with a spear, and immediately
        blood and water came [flowing] out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And he (John, the eyewitness) who has seen it has testified, and
        his testimony is true; and he knows that he is telling the truth, so that
        you also [who read this] may believe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "For these things took place to fulfill the Scripture, \u201CNot a
        bone of His shall be broken.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "And again another Scripture says, \u201CThey shall look at Him whom
        they have pierced.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And after this, Joseph of Arimathea\u2014a disciple of Jesus, but
        secretly for fear of the Jews\u2014asked Pilate to let him take away the
        body of Jesus; and Pilate gave him permission. So he came and took away His
        body. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Nicodemus, who had first come to Him at night, also came bringing
        a mixture of myrrh and aloes, [weighing] about a hundred [Roman] pounds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "So they took Jesus\u2019 body and bound it in linen wrappings with
        the fragrant spices, as is the burial custom of the Jews. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Now there was a garden at the place where He was crucified, and in
        the garden a new tomb [cut out of solid rock] in which no one had yet been
        laid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: Therefore, because of the Jewish day of Preparation, and since the
        tomb was nearby, they laid Jesus there.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Empty Tomb'
      title: The Empty Tomb
      number: 1
      content: '  Now on the first day of the week Mary Magdalene came to the tomb
        early, while it was still dark, and saw the stone [already] removed from
        the [groove across the entrance of the] tomb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So she ran and went to Simon Peter and to the other disciple (John),
        whom Jesus loved (esteemed), and said to them, \u201CThey have taken away
        the Lord out of the tomb, and we do not know where they have laid Him!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Peter and the other disciple left, and they were going to the
        tomb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the two were running together, but the other disciple outran
        Peter and arrived at the tomb first. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Stooping down and looking in, he saw the linen wrappings [neatly]
        lying there; but he did not go in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Simon Peter came up, following him, and went into the tomb and
        saw the linen wrappings [neatly] lying there;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and the [burial] face-cloth which had been on Jesus\u2019 head, not
        lying with the [other] linen wrappings, but rolled up in a place by itself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the other disciple, who had reached the tomb first, went in too;
        and he saw [the wrappings and the face-cloth] and believed [without any doubt
        that Jesus had risen from the dead]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For as yet they did not understand the Scripture, that He must rise
        from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then the disciples went back again to their own homes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But Mary [who had returned] was standing outside the tomb sobbing;
        and so, as she wept, she stooped down and looked into the tomb; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and she saw two angels in white sitting there, one at the head and
        one at the feet, where the body of Jesus had lain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And they said to her, \u201CWoman, why are you crying?\u201D She
        told them, \u201CBecause they have taken away my Lord, and I do not know
        where they have laid Him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'After saying this, she turned around and saw Jesus standing there,
        but she did not know that it was Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Jesus said to her, <JESUS>\u201CWoman, why are you crying? For whom
        are you looking?\u201D</JESUS> Supposing that He was the gardener, she replied,
        \u201CSir, if you are the one who has carried Him away from here, tell me
        where you have put Him, and I will take Him away.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Jesus said to her, <JESUS>\u201CMary!\u201D</JESUS> She turned and
        said to Him in Hebrew, \u201CRabboni!\u201D (which means, Teacher). "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Jesus said to her, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>Do not hold Me, for
        I have not yet ascended to the Father; but go to My brothers and tell them,
        \u2018I am ascending to My Father and your Father, and to My God and your
        God.\u2019\u2009\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Jesus among His Disciples'
      title: Jesus among His Disciples
      number: 18
      content: 'Mary Magdalene came, reporting to the disciples that she had seen
        the Lord and that He had said these things to her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So when it was evening on that same day, the first day of the week,
        though the disciples were [meeting] behind barred doors for fear of the Jews,
        Jesus came and stood among them, and said, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>Peace
        to you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'After He said this, He showed them His hands and His side. When the
        disciples saw the Lord, they were filled with great joy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Jesus said to them again, <JESUS>\u201CPeace to you; as the
        Father has sent Me, I also send you</JESUS> [as My representatives].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And when He said this, He breathed on them and said to them, <JESUS>\u201CReceive
        the Holy Spirit.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>If you forgive the sins of anyone they are forgiven</JESUS>
        [because of their faith]; <JESUS>if you retain </JESUS>the sins of anyone,
        they are retained [and remain unforgiven because of their unbelief].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But Thomas, one of the twelve [disciples], who was called Didymus
        (the twin), was not with them when Jesus came. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So the other disciples kept telling him, \u201CWe have seen the Lord!\u201D
        But he said to them, \u201CUnless I see in His hands the marks of the nails,
        and put my finger into the nail prints, and put my hand into His side, I
        will never believe.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Eight days later His disciples were again inside the house, and Thomas
        was with them. Jesus came, though the doors had been barred, and stood among
        them and said, <JESUS>\u201CPeace to you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then He said to Thomas, <JESUS>\u201CReach here with your finger,
        and see My hands; and put out your hand and place it in My side. Do not be
        unbelieving, but</JESUS> [stop doubting and] <JESUS>believe.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Thomas answered Him, \u201CMy Lord and my God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Purpose of Writing this Gospel'
      title: Purpose of Writing this Gospel
      number: 29
      content: "Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CBecause you have seen Me, do you
        now believe? Blessed</JESUS> [happy, spiritually secure, and favored by God]
        <JESUS>are they who did not see</JESUS> [Me] <JESUS>and yet believed</JESUS>
        [in Me].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'There are also many other signs (attesting miracles) that Jesus performed
        in the presence of the disciples, which are not written in this book; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: but these have been written so that you may believe [with a deep,
        abiding trust] that Jesus is the Christ (the Messiah, the Anointed), the
        Son of God; and that by believing [and trusting in and relying on Him] you
        may have life in His name.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Appears at the Sea of Galilee'
      title: Jesus Appears at the Sea of Galilee
      number: 1
      content: '  After this Jesus revealed Himself again to the disciples at the
        Sea of Tiberias (Galilee). And He did it in this way: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Simon Peter, and Thomas who is called Didymus (the twin), and Nathanael
        from Cana of Galilee, as well as [John and James] the sons of Zebedee, and
        two others of His disciples were together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Simon Peter said to them, \u201CI am going fishing.\u201D They said,
        \u201CAnd we are coming with you.\u201D So they went out and got into the
        boat; and that night they caught nothing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'As morning was breaking, Jesus [came and] stood on the beach; however,
        the disciples did not know that it was Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CChildren, do you have any fish</JESUS>
        [to eat along with your bread]?\u201D They answered, \u201CNo.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CCast the net on the right-hand
        side of the boat (starboard) and you will find some.\u201D</JESUS> So they
        cast [the net], and then they were not able to haul it in because of the
        great catch of fish. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then that disciple (John) whom Jesus loved (esteemed) said to Peter,
        \u201CIt is the Lord!\u201D So when Simon Peter heard that it was the Lord,
        he put on his outer tunic (for he was stripped for work) and threw himself
        into the sea [and swam ashore]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But the other disciples came in the small boat, for they were not
        far from shore, only about a hundred yards away, dragging the net full of
        fish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So when they got out on the beach, they saw a charcoal fire set up
        and fish on it cooking, and bread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CBring some of the fish which you
        have just caught.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Jesus Provides'
      title: Jesus Provides
      number: 11
      content: 'So Simon Peter went aboard and hauled the net to land, full of large
        fish, a hundred and fifty-three [of them]; and although there were so many,
        the net was not torn.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CCome </JESUS>and have breakfast.\u201D
        None of the disciples dared to ask Him, \u201CWho are You?\u201D They knew
        [without any doubt] that it was the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Jesus came and took the bread and gave it to them, and likewise the
        fish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Love Motivation'
      title: The Love Motivation
      number: 14
      content: 'This was now the third time that Jesus appeared to the disciples,
        after He had risen from the dead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So when they had finished breakfast, Jesus said to Simon Peter, <JESUS>\u201CSimon,
        </JESUS>son of John, do you love Me more than these [others do\u2014with
        total commitment and devotion]?\u201D He said to Him, \u201CYes, Lord; You
        know that I love You [with a deep, personal affection, as for a close friend].\u201D
        Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CFeed My lambs.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Again He said to him a second time, <JESUS>\u201CSimon, </JESUS>son
        of John, do you love Me [with total commitment and devotion]?\u201D He said
        to Him, \u201CYes, Lord; You know that I love You [with a deep, personal
        affection, as for a close friend].\u201D Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CShepherd
        My sheep.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Our Times Are in His Hand'
      title: Our Times Are in His Hand
      number: 17
      content: "He said to him the third time, <JESUS>\u201CSimon, </JESUS>son of
        John, do you love Me [with a deep, personal affection for Me, as for a close
        friend]?\u201D Peter was grieved that He asked him the third time, <JESUS>\u201CDo
        you</JESUS> [really] <JESUS>love Me</JESUS> [with a deep, personal affection,
        as for a close friend]?\u201D And he said to Him, \u201CLord, You know everything;
        You know that I love You [with a deep, personal affection, as for a close
        friend].\u201D Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CFeed My sheep.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  <JESUS>I assure you </JESUS>and most solemnly say to you, when
        you were younger you dressed yourself and walked wherever you wished; but
        when you grow old, you will stretch out your hands and arms, and someone
        else will dress you, and carry you where you do not wish to go.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now He said this to indicate the kind of death by which Peter would
        glorify God. And after saying this, He said to him, <JESUS>\u201CFollow Me</JESUS>
        [walk the same path of life that I have walked]!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Peter turned and saw the disciple whom Jesus loved following them;
        the one who also had leaned back on His chest at the supper and had said,
        \u201CLord, who is it that is going to betray You?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So when Peter saw him, he asked Jesus, \u201CLord, and what about
        this man [what is in his future]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CIf I want him to stay alive until
        I come</JESUS> [again], <JESUS>what </JESUS>is that to you? You follow Me!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So this word went out among the brothers that this disciple (John)
        was not going to die; yet Jesus did not say to him that he was not going
        to die, but only, <JESUS>\u201CIf I want him to stay alive until I come</JESUS>
        [again], <JESUS>what </JESUS>is that to you?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'This is the same  disciple who is testifying to these things and
        has recorded them; and we know [without any doubt] that his testimony is
        true.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And there are also many other things which Jesus did, which if they
        were recorded one by one, I suppose that even the world itself could not
        contain the books that would be written.
      comments: []
